title: apple cobbler
directions: Cook apples in 2 cups water.
Melt butter in glass dish.
Add cinnamon.
Pour apples into butter.
Mix remaining ingredients together; pour over apples.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, then bananas and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Add vinegar and milk to make buttermilk.
Then add baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Gradually add flour.
Fold in egg whites last.
Pour in greased loaf pan and bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate or cut fine cabbage.
Mix together well; let stand. Refrigerate overnight.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Make a syrup of sugar, water, butter and salt.
In a greased casserole, place whole or sliced cooked potatoes.
Pour syrup over potatoes.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 45 minutes. Baste often.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine eggs, oil and Bisquick.
Stir in peppers, onion, garlic and cheese.
Stir in squash.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray or oil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: three "p" salad
directions: Mix all together.
Option:
Use 1/2 mayonnaise and 1/2 sour cream.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Put seasoning mixture in pan with water and bring to boil. Brown together rice and noodles from soup package in margarine. When brown, add to water.
Cover and cook about 30 minutes or until done.
Add more water, if needed.
Serves 6.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add cornflakes, then spread cabbage over cornflakes.
Mix soup, onion, milk, cheese and Miracle Whip together and pour over cabbage.
Top with an additional 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup cornflakes.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peach pushover
directions: Pour undrained peaches into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in orange extract and 1 tablespoon butter.
Sprinkle with cake mix. Dot with remaining 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in large bowl. Blend well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture. Stir in nuts.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Bake in loaf pans.

title: brandy slush
directions: Mix and freeze.
To serve, fill glasses half full and add 7-Up or Squirt.

title: cajun meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coarsely chop the onion.
In a large skillet warm the oil over high heat.
Add the onion, garlic, chili powder, salt, paprika and cayenne.
Cover, reduce the heat to low and cook, stirring often, until the onions are softened but not brown.
Remove the skillet from heat.
Stir in tomato juice and set mixture aside to cool.
In a large bowl, combine beef and pork. Add the bread, eggs, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, hot pepper sauce and onion mixture and mix lightly.
Place mixture in a 9 x 5-inch pan.
Place the mixture into form.
Bake for 55 minutes or until meat is done.
Stand for 10 minutes.

title: overnight sausage souffle
directions: A day ahead, layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese in buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Beat eggs and stir in mustard, salt and milk.
Pour over ingredients in dish.
Cover and refrigerate. Next morning, bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve while still puffy.

title: busy day pork chop dinner
directions: Use roasting pan large enough
to
lay pork chops single layer.
Slice potatoes
thin
and layer on top of chops.
Slice onions (enough for only
layer)
and put on top of potatoes. Dot with butter
and
salt
and
pepper
to
taste.
Cover with aluminum foil sealing sides tightly.
Cook in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until meat is done and potatoes are tender.
Serve with a green salad for a quick, nourishing dinner.

title: italian biscuits
directions: Mix together until smooth and spread in greased cookie sheet. Bake in 400° oven for 15 or 20 minutes.
When done, slice and toast until done.

title: homestyle chicken vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; simmer until vegetables are tender (approximately 10 minutes). Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chili casserole
directions: Place alternately in layers chili con carne and chips. Top with cheese and bake 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas chicken
directions: Place layers of tortillas, torn and soaked in chicken broth on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add, in layers, the green pepper, cheese, chicken and garlic salt.
Mix soups and pour over layers.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, egg, milk and Bisquick.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds, batter may still be slightly lumpy.
Stir in nuts and bananas.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until toothpick stuck into center comes out clean. Bake at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add scalded milk last.
Melt butter in milk.
Bake about 30 or 40 minutes at 350° until thoroughly hot.
Turn down to 300° and cook until golden brown.
Better to let stand 1 hour before baking.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and make into small balls.
Cook in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and flour.
Cook until thickened.
Cool. Prepare Dream Whip as directed.
Fold in coconut and cherries (chopped) except reserve 12 for top.
Slice bananas in bottom of crust; sprinkle nuts over bananas.
Spread pineapple filling over this.
Top with Dream Whip and whole cherries.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: cranberry-cherry jello
directions: Add boiling hot water to Jell-O and stir to dissolve.
When Jell-O starts to get firm, add cranberry/orange relish and crushed pineapple.
Mix together and pour into a mold or bowl.
Chill until firm.
Has a delicious and refreshing flavor.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Beat eggs with enough flour to make like pancake dough.
Cut pork in cubes and coat with egg batter.
Deep-fry in oil until light brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside.
Cut peppers and onions in strips.
In skillet, prepare sweet and sour mix with reserved pineapple juice.
Heat until thickened.
Add green peppers and onions.
Cook until tender.
Add pork; heat.
Add pineapple chunks.
Serve over fried rice.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together cheese, flour, sugar and cheese crackers.
Place pineapple in bottom of square pan.
Pour dry mix on top.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: portales peanut pie(also called farmer's peanut pie)
directions: Combine the eggs, butter, corn syrup, sugar and vanilla in
a mixing
bowl
at low speed.
Stir in peanuts and scrape mixture into
chilled
pie	shell.	Bake in a 350° oven until mixture is set, about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Cook apples, 1/4 cup oleo, sugar and cinnamon on stove until tender.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: easy casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and milk to your desired consistency. Heat through until done.
If meatballs are thawed, one-half hour is enough.
If meatballs are frozen, one hour.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix lightly, roll out and cut in straws.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes about 60 six-inch straws.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place all ingredients in casserole, sprinkling onion mix over top.
Cover tightly. Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: party potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes for 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients except corn flakes.
Place in glass baking dish. Sprinkle with corn flakes.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour.

title: confetti potatoes
directions: Saute zucchini and celery in margarine until crisp-tender and add mushroom slices.
Cook 1 minute.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Serve over potatoes.
May add a drop of sour cream if desired.

title: grilled-marinated pork loin
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pork, in a saucepan.
Bring to boil, remove from heat and stir; let cool down.
Slice pork roast into 4 slices and pierce each side of chops with a fork several times.
Put pork chops in a 1-gallon Ziploc bag and pour marinade over; seal and refrigerate 24 hours.
Cook pork chops over medium hot coals on uncovered grill about 25 minutes, basting with excess marinade and turning several times.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Use liquid with all canned items.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Bake 1/2 hour at 300°.
Mix 1/2 cup water with 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pour over pudding.
Bake another 1/2 hour at 300°.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook 4 minutes on High.
Stir and cook 4 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla. Cook 2 minutes.
Stir in soda and pour onto cookie sheet.
Let cool.

title: hoover cake
directions: Combine sugar, brown sugar and shortening.
Mix until creamy. Mix eggs and buttermilk and add to sugar mix.
Sift flour, nutmeg, soda and baking powder.
Add in parts to sugar and buttermilk. Bake in cake pan, lightly greased, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheese bites
directions: Cream the butter and cheese together.
Add salt and pepper. Stir in flour; mix well.
Roll into marble size balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes. Be careful not to brown.
These taste best at room temperature.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Cream well. Add sugar, beating until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well. Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.

title: relish tray
directions: Mix sour cream and Ranch dip.
Put mixture in bowl.
Place remaining vegetables around bowl.

title: bavarian nut pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients and sift.
Add egg just enough to blend; add melted butter and combine.
Combine milk and water; add to mixture, beating only until batter is smooth.
Combine coconut and pecans; spread on bottom of unbaked pie crust.
Fill with chocolate mixture.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
First 15 minutes at 375°, then drop heat to 375°.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Drain salmon and save liquid. Mix flaked salmon, onion and red pepper. Add milk to salmon liquid until it measures 3/4 cup. Butter loaf pan. Beat eggs. Add salmon liquid with milk and eggs to salmon mixture. Add Special K cereal. Mix lightly. Bake in oven for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir contents of vegetable/seasoning packet, margarine and water in bowl.
Add stuffing crumbs and stir until water is absorbed.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: sugar-free cookies
directions: Mix well all ingredients in order given.
Chill an hour. Roll cookies into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Serves 18.

title: trifle
directions: Bake cake as directed on box, using 3 round cake pans.
(Pound cake may also be used.)
Prepare instant pudding as directed on box and mix with the Cool Whip.
Combine the fruit.
In large glass bowl, begin layering trifle, starting with cake, then the fruit, then the pudding, and repeat until all are in bowl.
Top with Cool Whip.
Make at least 5 hours before serving and refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook green pepper and onion in oil until tender (not brown). Blend in cornstarch with small amount of chicken stock and add remaining stock and soy sauce.
Stir in chicken.
Cook and stir until sauce is clear and thickened.
Add tomatoes (cut in thin wedges).
Serve over rice.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add melted shortening, milk and egg.
Mix just until blended.
Pour into a greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
May also be put in muffin pans. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown and wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Yields approximately 10 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Wash cauliflower pieces and place in a large mixing bowl.
In a small bowl combine Miracle Whip and dry seasons Italian seasoning.
Mix thoroughly and pour over cauliflower.
Add peas and bacon.
Place in a serving bowl and refrigerate.

title: cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients with enough mayonnaise to make a good spreading consistency.
Serve on sandwiches or crackers.

title: hermits
directions: Measure and sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar.
Blend well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add molasses and blend.
Add dry ingredients, about 1/3 at a time.
Mix well.
Mixture will be thick.
Add raisins and nuts.
Again mix well.
Lightly grease a jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch.
Spread mixture and bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except potatoes and ham, reserving 1/2 cup cheese for topping.
Heat well on stove.
Fold potatoes and ham into spinach mixture.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small pieces.
Chop onion.
Add cheese to broccoli and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over broccoli mixture.
Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: blueberry-cream cheese pie
directions: Combine ingredients for crust.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Saute onions in 4 tablespoons of melted butter. Stir in flour and water and cook until mixed. Blend in cheese.
Combine sauce with broccoli and eggs.
Put into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix crumbs with 2 tablespoons melted butter and sprinkle over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: cookie candy canes or valentine hearts
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a medium bowl, beat together butter, sugar, egg, vanilla and peppermint extracts until light and fluffy.
Add flour and baking powder, beating until blended. Divide dough into 2 equal portions. Stir red food coloring into 1 portion of dough, beating or kneading until well blended.
For each cookie, shape 1 teaspoon of each color dough into a 4-inch long rope, rolling back and forth until smooth, even ropes. Place 1 red rope and 1 white rope, side by side.
Press together lightly and twist.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheets.

Curve 1 end of cookie dough down to form handle of candy cane. Brush with slightly beaten egg white and sprinkle with red sugar crystals. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until edges begin to brown lightly. Remove cookies from baking sheets.
Cool on racks.

title: neiman marcus bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and eggs.
Makes a soft batter.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or Pyrex evenly.
May flour fingers to do this.
Cream together cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar.
You can add 6 ounce package of chocolate chips or 1 small can crushed and drained pineapple.
Pour over first layer in pan.
Bake 1 hour at 300° in regular oven.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and chill for 1 hour. Roll into small balls and bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat the oil, sugar and vanilla; add the next 5 ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook meat until brown, stirring as you go; drain well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with pizza sauce and cheese. Combine biscuit mix, milk and eggs. Beat until smooth and pour over the top evenly. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick easy ol'fashion'd biscuits
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder; cut or rub in shortening. Add milk to make a soft dough.
Knead lightly on floured board or cloth.
Roll 1/4-inch thick and cut.
Bake in a 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: boursin cheese
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese, then blend garlic into mixture. Add onion and dry Italian dressing; mix well.
Blend in milk. Serve at room temperature.

title: ham loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Coat a baking sheet with olive oil cooking spray. Place chicken breasts between 2 pieces of plastic wrap and pound to 1/4-inch thickness. Arrange 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of cheese on each chicken breast. Starting from shorter end of chicken, roll up breast into a tight pinwheel. Tuck in ends. Secure with toothpicks. Place flour, honey, mustard and bread crumbs in 3 separate shallow bowls. Add chicken to flour; turn to coat. Transfer chicken to honey mustard; turn to coat. Place chicken in bread crumbs; turn to coat. Transfer chicken to prepared baking sheet and coat with cooking spray. Bake until chicken is golden brown and cooked through, about 40 minutes. Remove toothpicks and serve.

title: buttercream frosting for decorating
directions: Will keep up to 2 months in refrigerator.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water in a large bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Add flour gradually (3 1/2 cups) until stiff dough forms.

title: nutty buddies
directions: Cover large flat pan with foil; line with graham crackers. Sprinkle chopped nuts over crackers.
Mix butter, margarine and sugar; boil 3 minutes and pour over crackers and nuts.
Place in 325° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add half the chipped beef. Shape into 2 balls, then roll in remaining beef to cover outside of balls.
Store in aluminum foil.

title: taffy candy
directions: Mix sugar, molasses, vinegar and water together, then let boil until it gets stringy and all cooked together.
With buttered hands, put some in your hands and pull until thin.
Break into pieces.
Put on wax paper and let cool, then eat.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Press chopped pecans into the pie crust before baking.
Let the crust cool completely.
Prepare the Dream Whip as directed on package only use no flavoring.
Beat to peaks.
Add cream cheese (let the cream cheese reach room temperature).
Add the confectioners sugar and beat until creamy.
Put this mixture in the cooled pie crust.
Put 1/2 can blueberries on each pie.
Use a teaspoon to put small amounts all over the mixture, then spread. Keep chilled.

title: chow mein clusters candy
directions: Melt morsels in double boiler.
Stir in noodles and nuts until well coated.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper to set.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients (except flour) in a large bowl (knead with hands), meat first, then dry ingredients, then remaining ingredients.
Set in covered bowl in refrigerator to blend for 1 to 2 hours.
Form into loaf and bake in uncovered, greased pan at 300° for about 1 3/4 to 2 hours.
Make gravy from drippings, using the 2 tablespoons flour and water.
(Best if made and baked one day and served the next.)

title: bisquick mix
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, dry milk and salt.
Cut in 1 3/4 cups shortening until mixture resembles coarse corn meal. Store in airtight container.
Needs no refrigeration if using vegetable shortening.

title: cajun shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and heat.
Put shrimp in casserole dish, not cleaned.
Put sauce over and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge
directions: Stir often and regular.
Cook sugar, milk and margarine after it starts to boil for 9 minutes on medium-high heat.
Remove from stove, add chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Alternate chocolate drops and marshmallow cream until all is used.
Beat with mixer.
Put on greased platter.
Cool, then cut in squares.

title: herb and cheese pull aparts
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in small bowl; stir well.
Set aside.
Unroll crescent rolls into two rectangles; connect ends to make one long rectangle.
Press perforations to seal.
Spread cream cheese mixture over crescent rolls to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Roll, starting at long side, jellyroll fashion.
Pinch edge to seal.

title: crawfish jambalaya
directions: Saute in oleo the peppers, onions and celery.
Add scrambled sausage.
Add Rotel, tomatoes, water, rice.
Fifteen minutes before done, add crawfish.
Cook
on low heat.
Do not overcook.

title: pistachio inside-outside cake
directions: Blend all ingredients for cake in a large bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool 15 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: brussels sprouts and carrots
directions: Simmer 2 packages frozen Brussels sprouts and 4 large carrots, sliced in 1/2 cup boiling water with 1 teaspoon salt added.
Cook until tender.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup and heat thoroughly.
Add 1/2 cup grated cheese and stir slightly.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello and water in blender.
Add cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into jello mold.

title: orange muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add butter, egg, milk and sugar; stir until moistened.
Stir in orange rind and juice. Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling two-thirds full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields about 6 muffins.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream oil, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat thoroughly and add bananas.
Sift dry ingredients; add nuts and raisins. Fold into creamed batter.
Bake in two greased and floured 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Invert on wire racks and cool.
Ice when completely cool.

title: egg white cookies
directions: Beat egg whites well.
Add brown sugar very slowly.
Beat until it holds high peaks.
Fold in broken pecans.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by tablespoonful.
Bake in 250° preheated oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet for 10 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Place 9-inch round cake pan on a burner over medium heat. Melt together butter and brown sugar.
Place 4 pineapple rings with maraschino cherries in the center of the pan.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and pour the cake batter over the pineapple rings.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Fold apples and nuts together.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased large casserole.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers or crushed onion rings. Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Put foil over top until almost done so crackers will not get too brown.

title: pickled beets
directions: Pack in jars (using lots of dill).
Pour in brine.
They will seal.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Rub meat with salt and ginger; put in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients, except fat and gingersnaps, in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over meat.
Cool, cover and put in refrigerator for 3 days, turning meat once each day.

title: marinated veggie salad
directions: Combine dressing mix with oil and vinegar.
Mix well.
Let set while preparing salad.
Bring frozen veggies to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes.
Drain immediately and put in cold water to stop cooking process.
Drain again.
Add remaining veggies and toss lightly. Pour dressing over veggies and chill.
Keeps a long time refrigerated.

title: irish fruit cakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
In separate bowl, mix salt, cinnamon and nutmeg with flour.
Alternately add eggs and flour mixture to creamed butter and sugar.
Add fruit, lemon rind, whiskey and lemon juice.
Place in a well-greased pan and bake at 350° for an hour, then at 300° for another hour.
Remove from oven and let cool.
When cool, pour more whiskey on top and wrap in foil.
Store in airtight tin.
Makes 3 cakes.

title: egg noodles
directions: Beat eggs and egg shell water together.
Add flour slowly to a stiff dough.
Size of eggs may require more or less flour.
Roll very thin and let set an hour or so.
Sprinkle with flour.
Roll tightly and slice into thin slices. Unroll slices and cut into desired size.
Cook in hot broth, adding a small amount at a time. After all are in the broth, lower heat to a simmer.
Cover and continue cooking until done.
Will take 1 to 1 1/2-quarts of broth for this amount of noodles.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix ranch dressing as directed on package.
Add beans, onion, and black olives, and set in the refrigerator for at least 3 hours.
Just before serving add remaining ingredients.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute the fresh sausage until browned.
Add smoked meats, celery, onion and bell pepper.
Saute until translucent.
Add rice and saute until rice turns milky white.
Add remainder of ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce to a simmer. Cook without stirring for 25 minutes.
Taste check for seasoning and toss in green onions.
Cook for 5 minutes more before serving.

title: spicy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except catsup.
Spoon into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Spoon catsup over meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie
dough on 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake cookie dough at 350°
for
8 minutes.
Cool and mix cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Add
1 teaspoon milk to get smooth and spread over baked and cooled cookie.	Cover with bananas.
Completely cover bananas with
strawberry
glaze.
Now use your artistic creativeness to arrange fruit.
Use whatever fruit that makes it appetizing.

title: spinach casserole(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Pour into greased crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours. Recipe may be doubled, if desired.

title: zucchini or yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion in boiling, slightly salted water for about 3 minutes (squash will still be a little crisp).
Drain.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten egg, water, salt and yeast last.
Add flour and mix well, making dough. Put in a gallon Ziploc bag with 2 tablespoons corn oil.
Seal and put into the refrigerator.
Keeps one week. Take out amount you want and make rolls 2 to 3 hours before time to bake.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: orange salad
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin and stir well.
Stir in sherbet.
Drain pineapple and oranges; add to gelatin.
Serves 12.

title: crab foo yung
directions: Mix crabmeat with ginger juice and wine.
Beat egg whites stiff; add salt and cornstarch.
Heat oil and let it spread over frying pan.
Mix crabmeat and milk with egg whites.
Pour into frying pan.
Stir constantly until it thickens.
Remove to plate and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve hot.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini according to directions on box.
Drain and wash with cold water.
In a large bowl, combine pasta with all ingredients and mix well.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into dry cake mix.
Reserve 1 cup mixture.
Pat remaining mixture lightly into a 9 x 13-inch pan, building up 1/2-inch edge.
Spread 2 cans cherry pie filling over cake mixture to within 1/2-inch of pan edge.
Blend 1/2 cup chopped nuts and the 1 cup reserved mixture.
Sprinkle over top. Bake 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: icebox vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables in a large bowl; set aside.
In saucepan, combine sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; cool slightly.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Will keep up to one week.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add milk.
Put in a thick pan; cook on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Use egg whites and sugar, beaten, for meringue.
Put in cooked pie shell; top with meringue.
Broil until brown.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Pour in large baking dish.
Add soups, water and rice.
Mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes uncovered, then 30 minutes covered.

title: lemon cake
directions: Cream
butter
and eggs well.
Add 2 eggs and mix until all is	creamed.
Sift	dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and milk until all is well mixed.
Add raisins and nut meats. Pour
in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese ball(appetizer)
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Chop green onions and mushrooms very fine and drain well.
Cut beef fine and mix all ingredients, except pecans.
Shape into a ball and roll in finely chopped pecans. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Peel and dice eggplant.
Cook until tender, drain and mash. Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Beat egg, add all ingredients and mix.
Sprinkle the 1/3 cup of Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: squash casserole(main dish)
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender.
Brown ground meat; drain. Mix remaining ingredients together; drain squash.
Layer: squash, sour cream mixture and ground meat.
Repeat layers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with grated cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, salt, corn syrup, butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spread pecans on bottom of crust.
Cover with filling.
Place in oven; lower temperature to 350°.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: coconut pie without crust
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and baking powder.
Add well-beaten eggs, then add milk, vanilla, melted oleo and coconut.
Bake in 10-inch pie plate at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken, carrots, peas and vegetables in a big bowl.
Mix it up real good.
Then cook it until done.
After it cools off eat it.

title: orange chicken and rice wok
directions: Heat oil in wok and stir-fry chicken until browned.
Drain. Reduce heat and stir in combined mayonnaise, juice and brown sugar. Add rice and green pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add orange and pineapple.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes so that the rice will "process".
Makes 4 servings.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: potato salad(italy)
directions: Combine salad dressing mix with mayonnaise.
Blend in warm potatoes, celery and olives.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: reid's red hot chicken delight
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly together, except chicken. Marinate chicken for 8 hours before serving.
Cook on gas grill at lowest heat setting for 2 hours, turning occasionally.
Baste with sauce frequently.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Put all ingredients except flour in a large bowl.
Mix until creamy. Add flour.
Mix well.
Make small balls the size of a walnut.
Dip lightly in flour to prevent sticking to hands.
Put on cookie sheet; crisscross with fork dipped in sugar. Bake for 11 to 13 minutes in a 350° oven.
Dough handles well if allowed to chill.
Make sure you aren't using up all the peanut butter in the house or people may get mad at you!

title: quick skillet lasagna
directions: Lightly brown meat in heavy skillet.
Sprinkle 1/2 of spaghetti sauce mix over meat.
Spread cottage cheese in layer over meat.
Next, arrange uncooked noodles in layer.
Sprinkle with remaining spaghetti sauce mix, basil, parsley flakes and salt.
Add tomatoes with liquid and water, being sure all is moistened.
Cover tightly and simmer about 30 to 35 minutes or until noodles are done.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Return cover and let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crab bisque
directions: Blend cream cheese, melted butter, sherry and Worcestershire sauce until smooth.
Stir in crab meat.
Serve hot with Melba toast.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, Worcestershire sauce, seasoned salt and onion powder; mix well.
Stir in oats, carrot and parsley.
Combine beef and pork; add to egg mixture and mix well.
Press into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Top with ketchup. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until no pink remains.
Drain. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hummus
directions: In food processor or blender, combine beans, lemon juice, tahini paste, garlic salt and pepper until smooth.
Add olive oil and mix well.

title: katherine's pie crust
directions: Mix and pour into pie pan; press to shape crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.

title: shrimp and crab dip
directions: Mix first two ingredients and spread on cream cheese mixture, but not all the way to the edges. Spread shrimp and crab meat on top of all. Keep refrigerated for one hour ahead of serving time. Best served with Ritz crackers.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Drain cucumbers; mix with remaining ingredients.
Makes approximately 20 sandwiches.
Cut in desired shapes.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Add sugar.
Blend in egg, then milk and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients. Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350°.
Good warm with a spread of peanut butter or jelly and glass of cold milk!

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together the butter, Crisco, brown sugar and white sugar. Add vanilla and eggs. Add flour and soda. Mix well. Add oats, then chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: creamy carrot salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Heat pineapple juice over low heat.
Add marshmallows, stirring until melted.
Add cream cheese and blend until smooth.
Dissolve gelatin into boiling water, cool and them combine marshmallows.
Mix and chill gelatin until consistency of unbeaten egg white; stir pineapple and carrots.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan and chill until firm. Cut into squares to serve.

title: holiday gift bread
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Gradually add 2 cups flour sifted with baking powder, mixing well after each addition.
Toss remaining flour with cherries and nuts; fold into batter.
Pour batter into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake in a 325° oven for 60 to 80 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Mix confectioners sugar and milk.
Glaze warm loaves.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Season and brown pork chops in oil.
Drain on paper towel. Butter casserole dish and put pork chops in dish, then potato slices and slices of onion.
Mix soup and milk and pour over all. Put foil on top and bake at 350° until chops are tender, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: boil cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa, butter and vanilla.
Bring to a boil; then add peanut butter, oatmeal and nuts (optional) for one minute.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Saute vegetables in butter for 30 minutes in large heavy pot.
Add seasonings, them shrimp.
Saute for one minute, then add flour and tomato paste.
Continue to saute for 3 minutes; add water, chicken bouillon and parsley. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: milnot fudge
directions: Stir together marshmallow cream and peanut butter in mixing bowl.
Cook sugar and Milnot until mixture reaches a soft ball stage.
Add the vanilla and pour over first mixture.
Beat until smooth.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; cool.
Add diced vegetables, then the dressing and McCormick Salad Supreme spice.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray and pour in peaches. Melt margarine in the microwave and add remaining ingredients; stir together and pour over peaches.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or cut back temperature and cook slower.

title: macaroni and cheese pie
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Drain immediately. Have all other ingredients mixed together and add to drained macaroni.
Place in casserole dish and top with layer of Ritz cracker crumbs.
Cook for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: bible cake
directions: Cream together Judges and Jeremiah.
Add Jeremiah.
Beat well. Gradually add Judges and 1 Samuel.
Add 1 Kings and Amos and beat. Add 1 Samuel, Nahum and Numbers.
Add 2 Chronicles.
Mix well. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: toffee
directions: Line a round cake pan with nuts.
Melt margarine in saucepan; add sugar, stirring constantly.
Boil until mixture turns a medium tan color (about 6 to 7 minutes) over medium heat.
Pour over nuts.
Place chocolate pieces on top, spreading chocolate as it melts.
Refrigerate until hard.
Break into pieces.

title: mother's and my favorite cake(1-2-3-4 cake)
directions: *If using raisins, chocolate chips, etc., add extra 1/2 teaspoon of baking powder.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Sprinkle graham crackers on butter, spread milk evenly across, sprinkle chocolate chips evenly, add coconut, spread pecans and press down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (325° if using glass) or until brown.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 12-inch pan, add ingredients in layers in order listed.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Don't overcook or it will stick and burn edges.
If using glass dish, lower temperature to 300°.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Place beef in a 2-quart micro-proof casserole.
Cover with casserole lid and cook on High 5 minutes, stirring once during cooking time.
Pour off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce and water; mix well.
Spread 1/3 of the meat sauce in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch micro-proof dish.
Arrange half of the uncooked noodles over sauce.
Spread with half the Ricotta.
Sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Double wrap tightly with plastic wrap.
Cook on High for 20 minutes.
Cook at 50% power for 15 to 20 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella.
Cook on High 2 1/2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve with additional Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pound chicken breasts to tenderize.
Brown.
Put in casserole dish.
Spread broccoli on top.
Mix all other ingredients, except crumbs, and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Put pretzels in plastic bag and crush with rolling pin; careful so as not to crush too fine.
Melt margarine; add sugar and mix with pretzel crumbs.
Press in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: no peek stew
directions: Layer in roaster in order; cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours. Don't peek during cooking time.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: *Blueberries, strawberries or raspberries can be substituted for the blackberries.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar in lard.
Add cream of tartar and soda to milk. Mix liquid ingredients with vanilla and eggs and add to sugar mixture.
Add salt to flour and sift.
Add enough to liquid mixture to make a dough that can be rolled out.
Roll it out on floured cloth or board and cut with large biscuit cutter.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown around edges. Store in a tightly closed container.
This recipe will make about 90 large cookies.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil the margarine, oil, cocoa and water.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Beat until mixed well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk. Then add eggs and vanilla.
Add this to the previous mixture.
Pour into greased 12 x 18 x 1-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Five minutes before cake is done, make the following icing.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Put spinach back in same hot pot.
Add cream cheese.
Break into chunks and stir into spinach.
Add the next 5 ingredients to spinach and cream cheese.
Pour into oiled pan dusted with bread crumbs.
Cover top of spinach mixture with cheese (buy chunk cheese), cut 1/2-inch thick.
If you want, you can buy package of cheese already sliced.
Cover top of spinach mixture.
Beat 1 egg, flour and water; pour over top of cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 9-inch square pan.

title: chocolate mice
directions: Pour your chocolate chips in a pot and boil until melted. Throw in a couple (3) of chunks of cooking wax.
When melted, take out your cherries.
Dip the cherries in the chocolate while sticking a Kiss on the end (pointy part out).
Then before the chocolate dries, stick 2 almonds in between the Kiss and cherry. After each mouse is dry, take red icing for the nose and eyes. Your cherry stem should stick out for the tail.
Now just let them dry and you are done and ready to eat.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed.
Cook and, when cool, cut into 1-inch squares.
Layer brownie squares in dish.
Mix chocolate pudding as directed.
Layer brownies and pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken mushroom dish
directions: Line Pyrex dish with chicken breasts.
Sprinkle finely chopped onion on top of chicken.
Pour Campbell's "golden mushroom soup" over chicken.
Pour 1/4 cup of cooking sherry on top of chicken and mushroom soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle fresh, sliced mushrooms on top of chicken. Bake for 15 minutes.
Serve with white or wild rice.

title: fruit punch (gold)
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1 cup hot water per box.
Add sugar and let cool.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: fried potatoes and onions
directions: Fry bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Place bacon on a paper towel and leave drippings in skillet.
Pare and slice or dice potatoes; wash in cold water and drain well.
Cut potatoes in even size pieces.
Put onion and potatoes in skillet with bacon drippings; salt and pepper to taste.
Fry, turning often so they cook and brown evenly.
When cooked, add crumbled bacon, turning to mix in bacon.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to box directions.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan and spread coconut and nuts into bottom of pan.
Pour prepared cake mix into pan.
Mix sugar, margarine and cream cheese together until smooth.
Pour over cake mix and marbleize with knife.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together all except chilies and cheese.
Put 1/2 mix in layer.
Top with chilies and cheese.
Add another layer.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour.

title: easy sausage balls
directions: Combine Bisquick, sausage and cheese.
Roll into small balls and bake for 12 minutes at 375° or until brown and crusty.
Let cheese get to room temperature before mixing.
For a different flavor, add a very small amount of finely, grated onion to mixture.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl well.
Pour in pie crust and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix celery, apples and walnuts.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: acapulco casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add remaining ingredients except last 2.
Cook and stir 3 minutes.
Put a layer of tortillas in bottom of 2-quart casserole and top with sauce mixture.
Continue until sauce is used.
Top with cheese and bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: condensed milk
directions: In blender combine both milks, sugar and oleo.
Process until smooth.
Chill overnight.
Keep in refrigerator or freezer. Makes 5 cups.
Can be used in recipes calling for condensed milk.

title: popovers
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add milk and combine slowly with flour and salt.
Add melted butter.
Pour into greased muffin tins preheated in 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Bake for 20 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 15 minutes longer.
This last dries out hollow centers and is vital for perfect popovers, which turn out to be golden brown puffs.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Boil 1 cup water, add butter and shortening.
Stir until melted.
Add sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix yeast in 1 cup warm water.
When dissolved, add to mixture.
Add 2 eggs.
Add 6 cups flour or enough to make thick dough.
Mix thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: happy apple cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and baking soda in a large bowl.
Mix with a large spoon.
Add apples, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into a greased and sugared Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool 15 to 20 minutes in pan; then turn out onto a serving plate.

title: corned beef dinner
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water for 7 minutes.
Drain. Combine all ingredients except crumbs, mixing very lightly.
Top with crumbs.
Bake in 2-quart casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix meat, onion and salt in a mixing bowl.
Roll meat balls 1-inch in diameter.
Brown in 1/2 cup oil of your choice, turning to brown on all sides.
Remove from oil; place in crock-pot on low heat.
Pour barbecue sauce over meat.
Cook about 30 minutes.
Use more sauce if needed.
Delicious.

title: raisin carrot muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger; stir in carrots, raisins and nuts.
Separately combine undrained pineapple, eggs, butter and vanilla; stir into dry ingredients until just blended.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake in 375° oven 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn out onto rack to cool.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion; drain grease.
Add water (about 6 cups) and bouillon; boil.
Add vegetables, tomatoes and anything else you would like.
Bring to a boil for 10 minutes.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
During this time, mix 3 tablespoons flour with 1/2 cup water; pour slowly into soup to thicken.
Add noodles.
Makes 7 servings.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, shortening and flour into crumbs.
Take out 1/2 cup of crumbs for the top.
Take 1 tablespoon crumbs and spread on bottom of pie crust.
To remaining crumbs, add molasses, egg, hot water and baking soda.
When mixture is all mixed together, pour into pie crust and sprinkle the 1/2 cup crumbs on top and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes; then bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice or mash the eggplant; place in a saucepan with about an inch of water.
Cook under slight pressure (with a tight cover) until soft.
Add salt (before cooking).
If there is no water left, add eggs and stir in melted butter, pepper, onion and oregano with breadcrumbs.

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Add a small amount of milk to desired consistency.

title: squash casserole
directions: Steam squash until tender with onions and butter.
When tender, mash and add rest of ingredients.
Mix together; season with salt and pepper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: appetizing stuffed caps
directions: Pull stems from mushrooms.
Wash and set caps aside.
Chop stems, ham and onions fine.
Saute in oleo.
Stuff caps with sauteed items, sprinkle with Parmesan and Swiss.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve hot or room temperature.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix well.
Use 3 tablespoons of mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: chocolate picnic cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; let stand 10 minutes.
Add sugars and margarine and stir until margarine melts.
Add eggs and mix.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add 1/2 package of chocolate chips.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle nuts and the rest of the chocolate chips on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 40 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until onion and pickles are chopped.

title: sad cake
directions: Cream the brown sugar and eggs.
Add Bisquick and vanilla.
Add rest of ingredients.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour in batter and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven down to 300° for about 30 minutes.
Cake will fall slightly when the oven is turned down. This makes it a very moist and chewy cake.

title: christmas ginger cookies
directions: Sift flour, ginger, cinnamon, cloves and baking soda.
Cream butter; gradually add the sugar, beating until fluffy.
Add the egg and molasses.
Beat until blended.
Add the dry ingredients slowly and mix well until blended.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill overnight. Roll out part of the dough on a floured board.
Cut out with cookie cutters.
Repeat this step until the dough is used.

title: italian biscote
directions: Combine flour and baking powder in bowl.
Beat together eggs, sugar, butter or margarine and vanilla or lemon.
Combine wet and dry ingredients and mix together with wooden spoon, then by hand. Roll small pieces of dough and twist and bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet.
Frost with thin frosting.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add extracts.
Mix well.
Sift flour, spices, salt and soda and add alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Blend well.
Pour into a 10-inch stem pan that has been greased and dusted with flour.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Do not overbake.
Remove cake from pan while still hot and brush on icing with pastry brush, covering top and sides.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1/4 pound of margarine and mix with the graham crackers. Put in
a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: vodka fizz
directions: Fill blender with ice and blend with the ingredients.

title: jezebel
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Refrigerate; mixture keeps for weeks.
Pour mixture over 8 ounce package cream cheese; serve with crackers.

title: egg and meat casserole
directions: Mix together beaten eggs and meat. Add onion, bread cubes, cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into an 11 x 9-inch greased baking dish. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.
Serve with muffins, coffee cake or fruit salad.

title: peppermint dessert
directions: Whip the Dream Whip and add the crushed peppermint sticks and marshmallows.
Mix together and pour onto graham cracker crust in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: fresh peach cake
directions: Bake and cool cake.
Cook pudding mix and milk together following package instructions, either in microwave or stove top. Stir in sour cream.
Cool mixture completely and spread on cooled cake.
Cover with sliced, fresh peaches (well drained canned or frozen peaches may also be used).
Spread dessert topping over peaches and sprinkle with nuts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes in tube pan at 300°.

title: glazed baby carrots
directions: Boil or steam carrots until done.
Melt butter on low heat. Stir in sugar, cornstarch and seasonings.
Cook and stir until thick.
Pour over drained carrots.

title: grandma madden's potato candy
directions: Beat eggs until stiff.
Add vanilla, then sugar, a little at a time, until no longer sticky.
Roll out on table with powdered sugar, using a handful at a time.
Spread on peanut butter and roll up.
Refrigerate to chill.
Then slice into pieces.
Put in a plastic container to store.
"You can add food coloring to the white mixture if you like a little color; nice for Christmas."

title: chicken rice
directions: Place chicken in a casserole; salt and pepper to taste.
Add the uncooked rice over chicken, then add the shredded cheese.
Add 2 cans of water to the soup; bring to boil.
After this mixture comes to boil, pour over the ingredients in the casserole dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour (or until the chicken is done).

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugars.
Add flour, sifted with cream of
tartar and soda.
Add vanilla.
Fold in pecans. Roll in small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Flatten with glass dipped
in
sugar.
Bake
at 350° for 10 minutes or until light tan.

title: mexican feast
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and chili mix. Layer chips, beef mixture, beans, mushroom soup, cheese soup and tomatoes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Stir once halfway through cooking. Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples and place upright in a small baking dish.
Drizzle with butter.
Combine nuts with sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle the mixture into the centers and over the tops of apples.
Bake at 375° for one hour.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops, place in the bottom of casserole dish. Slice potatoes and place on top of pork chops.
Put mushroom soup on top and cover.
Bake in oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into two cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.
Then frost.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzel sticks, oleo and sugar; press into 9 x 14-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Mix strawberry jello and boiling water. Add strawberries. Let chill to thicken. Beat cream cheese with sugar; add Cool Whip and mix well. Put cheese filling in cooled crust. Top with strawberry jello. Chill overnight.

title: eggplant salad
directions: Combine oil, lemon juice, oregano and garlic in large skillet.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until garlic is lightly browned.
Add eggplant and onion.
Stir to coat. Cook, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes or until eggplant is tender.
Remove from heat.
Transfer to medium serving bowl. Stir in zucchini, mushrooms, tomato and salt.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.
Stir before serving. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken in white wine sauce
directions: Broil chicken.
When cooked, place in pot with chicken broth and whole bottle of wine, onion and garlic.
Cook 20 minutes more. Take out chicken; pour in cream.
Stir and cook 5 minutes more. To thicken, prepare 3 to 4 tablespoons flour with water.
Pour in while stirring.
Return chicken.
Serve over cooked rice and fresh cooked mushrooms. Green beans top off the meal.

title: fiesta chicken
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Add vegetables and pasta and salsa.
Cover; simmer 8 to 10 minutes, until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cilantro. Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna cheese chowder
directions: Combine half (2 tablespoons) margarine, celery, onion and potato.
Cook over medium heat in medium saucepot approximately 15 minutes, stirring
often.
Stir in salt, pepper, thyme, dill weed and flour.
Add tomatoes, milk, tuna and parsley.
Heat, stirring, until soup is thickened and comes to boil.
Stir in cheese and half (2 tablespoons) margarine.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugar, egg, salt, baking soda and flour; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes or until golden.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: green grape delight
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix until smooth.
Gently fold in grapes and pecans.
Chill thoroughly about 2 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 4 to 6 people.
May be served as dessert or a salad.

title: chickpea spread
directions: Blend.
Use as spread, dip or dressing.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine all other ingredients and add to broccoli.
Cover the top with crumbs.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°, until brown in a 12 x 16-inch dish.

title: autumn fruit salad
directions: Mix whipped topping and mayonnaise together.
Toss apples and bananas in juice.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, cream sugar, margarine, sour cream and eggs (one at a time) on medium speed with mixer.
Add both flours and vanilla; beat well.
Grease and sugar the inside of tube pan. Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 5 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple pancake souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon; make a well in the center.

Add the egg substitute, milk and vanilla; whisk until thoroughly combined. Place the margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; place in the oven until the margarine is melted and sizzling, about 3 minutes. Add the apples and mix gently to coat.
Bake until the apples are heated through, about 5 minutes.
Pour the egg mixture over the apples; sprinkle with the brown sugar.
Bake until the souffle is puffed and golden and a knife inserted in the center comes out clean, about 35 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: orange delight
directions: Drain pineapple; add orange/strawberry jello.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill in covered container until ready to serve.

title: lela's dump cake
directions: Dump crushed pineapple in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread cherry pie filling over the pineapple.
Cut margarine through dry cake mix.
Sprinkle over the fruit.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
May be served with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend flour, butter and powdered sugar.
Press in pan with fingers. Bake at 350° until slightly brown, about 20 minutes. Place half of the berries in baked crust.
Add sugar and cornstarch. Boil until clear and thick.
Cool slightly and pour over berries in crust. Cool. Cover with Cool Whip.

title: healthy granola
directions: Great on other cereals, over ice cream or yogurt, as a trail snack or just for snacking on its own.

title: oatmeal honey toffee
directions: Pour melted shortening over rolled oats, mixing thoroughly. Add brown sugar, honey, salt and vanilla.
Pack firmly into well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in 325° oven about 12 minutes or longer until a rich brown color.
Let stand until completely cool.
Cut into bars.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy pot pie
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Boil boneless breast.
Let cool and chop.
In a boiler, add cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soup.
Drain Veg-All and add chopped chicken.
Stir well.
Pour ingredients in deep dish pie crusts.
Take 2 small pie crusts and top over deep dish.
Punch holes with fork before putting into oven.
Cook for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: meal-in-a-dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
In casserole dish, layer green beans, meat, Tater Tots and top with mushroom soup.
Sprinkle onions on top.
Cover and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and brown for 10 minutes longer.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add milk, egg yolks and salt. Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust and top with meringue, making sure to spread to edge of inside of crust.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until peaks are brown.

title: tofu taegu salad
directions: Wash vegetables and cut into 1-inch length pieces.
Cut tofu and tomatoes into small cubes.
Slice takuwan into strips.
Layer ingredients, beginning with watercress and ending with green onions.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together 1 1/2 cups of flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup oleo.
Pack in buttered, long, Pyrex dish.
Bake at 275° for 10 minutes.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Stir Bisquick, milk, cheese and chives together until moist.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until brown and puffy.

title: swedish pepperkakor
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add the beaten egg and syrup.
Sift the flour with dry ingredients and add to first mixture; mix well. Refrigerate the dough overnight.
Roll very thin, cut in shapes and bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate coconut slice
directions: Mix together.
Place in glass pan and cook on high for 4 minutes.
Mix icing ingredients (butter, sugar, vanilla, coconut and cocoa). with a little water, enough for spreading consistency. Spread onto warm bars. Cool 20 minutes and cut into squares.

title: diabetic candy
directions: Mix frosting, sweetener and salt with milk.
Add peanut butter, noodles and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and refrigerate.
Makes about 20 cookies.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend sugar and margarine.
Mix ingredients together.
Let raise 1 hour at room temperature.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 1 hour.

title: hanover tomato, cheese and herb tart appetizer
directions: For Crust:
Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add just enough ice water to hold dough together.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Roll out dough on lightly floured surface and transfer to an 11-inch tart pan with removable bottom.
Trim edges and freeze crust for 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pineapple and dry Jell-O (I use strawberry) over low heat until the Jell-O is dissolved.
Remove from heat; cool.
Stir in buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Chill and serve. (One cup chopped nuts are optional.)

title: cheese-broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli, onion, carrots and potatoes in enough water to cover until done.
Add bouillon cubes, milk and cheese; heat on low until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
Serve.

title: lemon cake with rhubarb
directions: Prepare lemon cake as directed on box, and pour this batter into a 9x13-inch baking dish.
Set aside.

title: amish pancakes
directions: Measure sifted flour into sifter and add baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat egg in bowl.
Add milk and blend.
Sift dry ingredients into this mixture gradually, beating after each addition.
Add melted shortening.
Beat with eggbeater until mixed. Bake on hot griddle, turning only once.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil and sugar, beat well.
Add vanilla and zucchini.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased pan.

title: sugar-free blueberry muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and oil.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in berries.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jello pinwheels
directions: Lightly spray 8 or 9-inch square pan with no stick spray.
Mix Jell-O and water in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart microwave bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir to dissolve completely.
Add marshmallows.
Microwave 1 minute or until marshmallows are melted. Stir until smooth.
Creamy layer will float to top.
Pour in pan. Refrigerate 45 minutes or until set.
Loosen edges with knife dipped in warm water.
Starting at 1 end, roll up tightly.
Cut in slices.
Serve immediately or refrigerate.

title: almond puff
directions: Cut 1/2
cup
of
butter in 1 cup of flour.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of water over mixture.	Mix with fork (almost like a pie
crust).
Round
into
a
ball	and
divide in half.
On ungreased
baking sheet, pat each half into a strip; should be inches apart.

title: instant hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix together. Store in airtight container. Use 1/4 cup of mix per mug of boiling water.

title: breakfast-egg casserole
directions: Cook sausage, preferably using iron skillet, until browned, stirring frequently; drain well.
In separate bowl, beat eggs with mustard and milk added.
In 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish, put layer of bread cubes, then sprinkle sausage and cheese layers. Second layer, pour mixture over top.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Can be made and refrigerated overnight!

title: poor man's stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown meat and onion in margarine.
Add other ingredients except soup.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.

title: wine marinade
directions: Mix the oil and wine together and then add the rest of ingredients.
Stir and let chill for several hours.
When ready to cook, pour over either prepared poultry or meat.
Chill 3 more hours.
Baste with the sauce during cooking of the meat.
Makes 3/4 cup sauce.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: coctail wieners
directions: In crockpot melt jelly, barbeque sauce and mustard.
Add wieners and simmer on low for 2 to 3 hours.

title: pot roast meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Shape into a loaf in center of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Peel and slice 1/4-inch thick the potatoes and onions.
Peel and quarter lengthwise the carrots.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour until vegetables are tender.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more to brown meat.

title: hamburger cheese quiche
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Mix together browned meat, eggs, milk, mayonnaise and cornstarch.
Stir in cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple roll-ups
directions: Blend 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Cut apple in 10 slices or in small chunks.
Roll apples in cinnamon and sugar. Flatten biscuits and put apple chunks in biscuits and roll up.
Lay in 13 x 9 casserole dish.
Put Sprite, 1 cup sugar and butter in saucepan and heat on medium until butter melts.
Pour over roll-ups.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with one tub of Cool Whip.
Spread over baked crust.
Mix puddings, lemon juice and milk.
Fold in other Cool Whip.
Pour in pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top for garnish.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Place in unbaked pie shell. Bake in hot oven (425°) for 15 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and continue baking for about 35 minutes or until custard is firm.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°f. 220°c. gas mark 7. In a large bowl beat the eggs lightly then stir in the rest of the ingredients in the order given. Pour into the pie crust, bake for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350°f. 180°c.
gas mark 4 and cook for a further 40-50 minutes or until a knife inserted into the center comes out clean. Cool on a wire rack.

title: marinated peas
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and set overnight in refrigerator. Drain well the next day and add the balance of recipe.
Before serving, mix with a small amount of mayonnaise.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need an 8-inch clay flowerpot lined with foil and silk flowers.

title: chili con carne
directions: Melt
butter
in a skillet.
Crumble in ground beef and let brown.
Add onion, beans and soup; continue to cook for 10 minutes.
Make
remaining ingredients into paste and blend in. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: maple pecan pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flavoring.
Add flour alternately with sour cream.
Blend in pecans that have been dusted with flour.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bonnie's ham rolls
directions: Slice the rolls horizontally. (They don't need to be separated and slice easily in the tray they come in.) Spread with butter, mixed with next 4 ingredients and top with ham and cheese. Cut apart. Heat at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dump and spread pineapple.
Add filling.
Spread.
Sprinkle with cake mix right out of the box. Sprinkle with nuts and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and vinegar.
Boil 5 minutes. Drain beets and add to sugar mixture.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally until beets are heated.
Add butter.
Salt and pepper, if desired.

title: orange eskimo salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix all ingredients together and freeze in oblong pan.
Take from freezer and cut into squares 30 minutes before serving.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and spices. Cream shortening and sugar. Add dry ingredients and tomato soup alternately. Stir in nuts and raisins. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Let stand before cutting. Makes one 8 x 4 x 3 loaf.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, eggs and cinnamon together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (glass pan).
Pour dry cake mix over pumpkin and mix.
Pat nuts into mix evenly.
Spoon melted butter over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool.
Top with cream cheese icing.

title: broccoli-rice casserole 2
directions: Cook broccoli and onion. Drain. Add rest of ingredients to broccoli and onion.
Pour in a
greased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar plum
directions: Combine milk, sugar and salt.
Cool.
Add yeast to warm water. Add 3 cups flour and beat.
Cream shortening, sugar, beaten eggs, nutmeg and vanilla.
Add to sponge mixture and beat.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup sugar together.
Add margarine.
Pat down into an 8 x 8-inch dish and around sides. Beat Dream Whip and chilled milk together until soft peaks form. Blend in sugar and softened cream cheese.
Put over top of crust. Spread cherries over top.
Chill.

title: praline strips
directions: Arrange graham crackers on ungreased 10 x 5 x 1-inch pan. Heat butter and sugar to a boiling point.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in nuts.
Spread over crackers and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cut while warm along cracker grooves.

title: hot sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: zucchini saute
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise in 6 sticks.
Saute, turning often, with onion and butter for 10 minutes or until tender.
Spoon into bowl.
Drizzle with soy sauce.
Sprinkle on almonds and parsley.

title: brad's fried potatoes with onion
directions: Heat olive oil in a pan.
Peel and wash potatoes; slice or thinly dice.
Peel and slice/dice onion.
Season within reason. Fry to your pleasure.
Yields 2 servings.

title: mandarin orange cake(pig pickin cake)
directions: Mix cake ingredients together for 2 minutes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 4 greased floured
9 inch pans. While cake is baking, make icing.

title: pumpkin juiceaka (orange julius)
directions: Blend together and serve immediately.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Wilt cabbage leaves in boiling water.
Mix ground beef, cooked rice, onion, salt, black pepper and egg together.
Trim off thickest part of stem from cabbage leaves.
Divide meat into equal portions and wrap each in a cabbage leaf and fasten with a wooden toothpick.
Brown cabbage rolls slightly in small amount of cooking oil.
Put in casserole dish and add 2 cans tomato sauce and 1/4 cup water.
Cover and cook slowly for about 40 minutes.

title: oobleck
directions: Pour ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Mix with fingers until it's a uniform and enjoyable consistency.
Brushes off easily when dry.
Refrigerate to keep fresh longer.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring ingredients to a boil.
Boil for 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: chicken soup
directions: Wash chicken and place in large pot (at least 6-quart) and cover with water.
Cover pot and bring to a boil; skim and simmer slowly for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat 2 or more hours or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and strain soup.
Refrigerate soup and then skim fat from cold soup.
Reheat to serve.
Save the carrots to slice into soup and add some cut up chicken, if you like, to reheated soup.

title: choco-date dessert
directions: Crush Oreos; spread over bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Reserve
1/4 cup for topping.
Bring dates and water to boil; reduce heat and simmer for 3 minutes.
Add marshmallows and chopped
nuts
to warm dates; stir until melted.
Cool to room temperature,
then spread over crumbs in dish.
Whip the cream. Add
vanilla; swirl over date mixture in dish.
Sprinkle
with reserved chocolate cookie crumbs.
Garnish with the walnuts. Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt into large bowl.
Blend in eggs, shortening, sugars, peanut butter and vanilla.
Then beat well. Mix in chips (and nuts).
Form into balls and place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: crock pot barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sauce in crock pot and add water until meat is covered.
Cook on high until meat falls apart when stirred with a fork.
Drain water and add barbecue sauce. Stir and simmer on low for 1 hour.

title: cold pack pickles
directions: Bring to rolling boil for 10 minutes 1 gallon of tap water. Add 3/4 cup salt.
Let water completely cool.
Pack each jar with cucumbers, grape leaf, couple leaves cabbage, 2 or 3 pods garlic and fresh dill.
Pour cooled water over cucumbers and seal.
Place jars on towels because jars will leak.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together with whisk.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
While cake is warm, blend frosting ingredients and spread on warm cake.

title: candied orange sweet potatoes
directions: Boil fresh sweet potatoes until tender; drain and remove skins, then slice. Mix brown sugar, margarine, orange juice, peels and salt in 8-inch skillet. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly. Add sweet potato slices; stir gently until glazed and heated through. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: kentucky spoon bread
directions: Melt margarine.
Add well beaten eggs and sour cream.
Mix well and add corns and corn bread mix.
Bake at 350° until brown and set in center, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: apple custard pie
directions: This gives 3 (9-inch) pies.
Bake at 400°
for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until set.
Put cinnamon on top.

title: peach bread pudding
directions: Grease a 2-quart baking dish with margarine.
Cut up peaches and save juice.
Reconstitute milk powder with juice drained from peaches.
Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes; lower heat to 350° and bake about 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: orange jello mold
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients.
Add sherbet and beat in Cool Whip. Stir in oranges and pineapple.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Add remaining Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with crushed nuts.

title: dried peach custard pie
directions: Mash and sweeten peaches with 3/4 cup sugar.
Spread peaches into unbaked pie shell.
Beat milk, eggs and remaining sugar; pour over peaches.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until custard is set and lightly browned.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in gradually the milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add chicken, salt and pepper.
Brown.
Add rice, soup mix and water.
Cover and cook about 1 hour.
Serve.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: spinach spread
directions: Drain the spinach.
Mix all together.
Refrigerate for a day. Good spread for rye bread or pumpernickel bread.

title: southern breakfast casserole
directions: Line slightly greased casserole with bread.
Spread hash over bread.
Make 4 deep indentations in hash with spoon.
Spoon cooked grits into holes.
Gently break one egg into each "hole" over grits.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until eggs are cooked to desired.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Place whipping cream in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat. Remove from heat and add chocolate morsels and remaining ingredients.
Stir until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth. Cover and refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups and water together.
Cut up chicken (or boneless chicken breasts).
Grease 14 x 10-inch pan.
Pour mixture over rice.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over all.
Do not add salt.
Cover and seal with foil.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: jambalaya("rich and spicy")
directions: In a Dutch oven, fry bacon to render fat, but not until it is crisp. Remove bacon and save. Add onion to bacon fat and cook until golden, about 5 to 6 minutes. Add green pepper and cook 3 minutes more. Add 1 cup rice. Stir to blend well. Add garlic, tomatoes, bacon, thyme, salt and black and red peppers.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour in chicken stock and bring to a boil. Add ham. Cover and place in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. Add shrimp and push them under mixture. Cover and bake 15 minutes more.
Do not overcook as rice will get soggy.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and sour cream
directions: Mix together the sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, Lawry's salt, paprika and pepper. Marinate chicken breasts overnight.
Prior to baking, roll chicken breasts in bread crumbs and place in baking dish.
Pour the butter over chicken. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: round steak sizzler
directions: Combine catsup, Worcestershire sauce, oil, and salt in a small bowl.
Cut steak in serving size pieces.
Place steak in a snug fitting bowl or double plastic bag.
Pour catsup mixture over steak.
Cover or fasten, and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: pumpkin loaf
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans.
Mix the ingredients and put in loaf pans. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: rancho beef bake
directions: Combine beans and tomatoes in 13 x 9-inch baking dish; spread evenly.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Shape into about 21 (1 1/2-inch) meat balls.
Arrange in 3 rows down center of filling.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Drop biscuits by tablespoon into 2 rows between meat balls.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Use the same flavor in Jell-O as in Kool-Aid.
In mixing your Jell-O, use hot water.
Makes 2 1/2 gallons.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each one.
Add bananas and nuts.
Add flour, sifted with soda, baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pineapple ice
directions: Place pineapple chunks and lemon juice in blender.
Puree until smooth.
Pour into plastic container or ice cube trays and freeze about 1 hour.
When mixture is slushy-frozen, puree again in blender until creamy.
Pour it back into freezer container and freeze at least 2 hours more.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; cut into bite-size pieces.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice and fold all ingredients together, with exception of cheese.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish . Sprinkle cheese on top with a few buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Wilt cabbage leaves in boiling water.
Mix next 6 ingredients thoroughly and form into rolls.
(Green pepper may be added if you wish.)
Roll a cabbage leaf around each roll and secure with toothpicks.
Cook cabbage rolls in can of cream of tomato soup to which 1 can water has been added.
