Cook until hamburger is done and cabbage leaves are tender.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef with salt in skillet, breaking up into small pieces.
Drain well.
Put meat into large bowl.
Add potatoes, soup, sour cream, cheese and onion.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes; top with French fried onions and bake 15 minutes more until bubbling.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Put broccoli in greased casserole dish.
Put chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine	soups,	egg,
mayonnaise
and lemon juice and blend.
Pour
over	broccoli
and chicken.	Sprinkle cheese over this.
Melt margarine and mix with dressing.
Pour over cheese layer.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Cut and mash artichoke hearts.
Mix with other ingredients and put in casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with Triscuits or other crackers.

title: one pan steak dinner
directions: In foil-lined pan, put steak, salt and pepper.
Add garlic salt, if desired.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°, covered with foil.

title: "dirt" cake
directions: You will also need silk or plastic flowers.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a quart jar with top and shake well.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Add cheese and chilies. In another pan or microwave, melt Velveeta or Cheez Whiz.
Add cream of mushroom soup and Pet milk.
Use corn or flour tortillas. Place 2 tablespoons of meat mixture on tortilla and roll* up to fill a casserole dish.
Pour remaining mixture over top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: egg noodle bake with golden raisins
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions; drain.
Rinse under water and drain again.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine the noodles with the cottage cheese and sour cream; set aside.
Melt the margarine in a small skillet.
Add onion; saute over medium heat until soft, about 5 minutes.
Combine onion with noodles.

title: cheezy corn chowder
directions: Combine the potatoes and enough water to cover in a soup pot. Cook until fork tender (not mushy) and drain.
Melt the butter in a large skillet and saute onions and bell pepper until tender but not browned.
Add sauteed vegetables and butter to potatoes along with remaining ingredients.
Return to medium high heat, stirring until dip is well blended into chowder.
Serve warm.

title: peanut butter butterscotch chex mix
directions: Melt together the peanut butter and butterscotch chips in double boiler or microwave.
Pour over Chex cereal and stir until cereal is covered.
Mix in chocolate chips.
Let cool.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix jalapeno, cornbread mix, buttermilk, eggs, creamed corn, garlic, Cheddar cheese, onion and bacon drippings. Stir until moistened. Bake at 400° for 45 to 55 minutes. Can be baked in muffin tin or iron triangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2.

title: nine-day cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, pepper and onions.
Combine the other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour mixture over vegetables and store in refrigerator
in covered jars.
Delicious for 9 days.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Beat together first 3 ingredients.
Then sift the rest together and add to the first mixture.
Place in greased bread pans.
Makes 3 medium-sized loaves.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat cake mix (dry), margarine and 1 egg in a large mixer bowl on low speed until crumbly.
Press lightly in ungreased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).

title: snapper in green sauce
directions: Mash garlic, parsley, flour and oregano in a food processor. Add the oil, water and vinegar little by little and process. Season fish with salt, black pepper and lime juice. Place some of the green sauce on a baking dish with some of the fish on top. Pour lime juice over the fish.
Continue adding layers of sauce, fish and lime juice.
End with fish on top.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes at 350° (or until done).
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Mix sugar and syrup. Cook 4 minutes. Add peanuts. Cook 4 minutes. Add teaspoon of soda, then pour into pan.

title: trail mix
directions: Toss all together in a bowl or bag.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush cookies. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding, milk and cream cheese.
Mix powdered sugar and Cool Whip in a
separate bowl. Add mixtures together and put on top of crushed cookies.

title: hawaiian cheesecake
directions: Prepare cake as directed and cool.

title: veal casserole
directions: Form veal into 6 patties.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese, salt, and pepper together.
Coat patties with crumb mixture and fry in hot oil until lightly browned on each side.
Pour spaghetti sauce on top of patties and cook on low heat for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle on any remaining crumbs.
Heat 5-10 minutes more.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Place the sugar, butter, lemon rind and juice and eggs in a heavy saucepan; cook gently over low heat until the mixture is thick but falls easily from a spoon.
Do not boil or let the mixture separate.
Remove from the heat and cool.
Store in the refrigerator in a tightly covered jar, or freeze.

title: tuscan pasta(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Cut cleaned greens into 1-inch strips.
Remove sausage from casings.
With oil, brown over medium-high heat.
Add garlic; cook just until you can smell it.
Add greens and tomatoes.
Cook until greens are wilted, about 3 minutes.

title: mini pizza
directions: Brown sausage (drain).
Brown hamburger (drain).
Return sausage and hamburger to pan and add 1 pound of cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Spread on thin sliced bread and cut in fourths.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Freeze and serve as needed. Makes about 80.

title: lettuce layer salad
directions: Tear
lettuce into bite sized pieces into a 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Layer vegetables listed on lettuce.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar
and
sour
cream
and
spread
over
all evenly. Garnish with cheese.
Chill for 8 to 12 hours.

title: cheesy pita pizza
directions: Lightly brush bread with 1 tablespoon of dressing.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Brush bread with half of the dressing remaining.
Top with cheese and desired pizza toppings.
Drizzle with remaining dressing.
Bake 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese begins to melt. Cut into 6 wedges.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chocolate banana cream pie
directions: Bake pastry shell and set aside.
Combine sugar, cocoa and cornstarch in medium saucepan.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Boil and stir 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour into bowl; press plastic wrap directly onto surface.
Cool to room temperature.
Cover bottom of crust with small amount of filling.
Arrange banana slices over filling. Cover with remaining filling.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream and banana slices.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Prepare cookie mix as directed on package.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Combine softened cream cheese and sugar and spread on top of cooked dough.
Drain pineapple and add sliced banana to juice and let soak.
Spread pineapple over cheese; sprinkle banana slices over the pineapple. Place oranges on top of banana slices.
Chop maraschino cherries and sprinkle on top of oranges.
Garnish with chopped nuts and flaked coconut.

title: mother's molasses cookies
directions: Add enough flour to make a soft dough to roll out.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake about 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: oatmeal nut muffins
directions: Mix well oats, flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Cut in margarine until coarse crumbs.
Beat in egg and buttermilk. Add nuts.
Stir just until moistened.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin cups.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Wonderful served with jelly at breakfast time.

title: icebox vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables in a large glass bowl; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Cool slightly and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: blondies
directions: Grease 12 x 9-inch pan.
Melt margarine.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in flour.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 18 to 24 blondies.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon and reserve 1/4 cup of drippings.
Crumble bacon and reserve 2 tablespoons.
Microwave beans as directed on package.
Drain well.
Add mushrooms and onion to 1/4 cup drippings in skillet.
Cook and stir on medium heat 10 minutes and drain.
Add bacon, hot cooked beans and pepper.
Mix lightly.
Pour cheese over mixture.
Garnish with crumbled bacon and serve.
Serves 10.

title: speedy spinach lasagne
directions: *May also add ground beef.

title: ribs
directions: Soak ribs 1 hour in salt water in cooler.
Take out and put in broiler pan. Cover with Carolina Treat.
Cook until brown with Kraft barbecue sauce and honey.
Put in warm oven at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Drop nuts in bottom.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix 3/4 cup brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and place in a bag.
Add cut up biscuits and shake until biscuits are covered.
Place biscuits in Bundt pan.
Boil the butter or margarine, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over biscuits and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine liquids.
Add spices and stir until well blended.
Add vegetables and stir.
Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours. Serves 8 to 10.
Serve cold.

title: silver dart lodge oatcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together, add eggs.
Mash bananas with fork and add lemon juice.
Mix into the creamed mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add.
Add nuts.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-pound loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: little cheese and tomato pizzas
directions: Turn a broiler on to medium heat.
Separate the muffins into halves.
Slice the tomatoes.
You will need 8 slices.
Lay the sliced English muffins on a pan, bottom side up.
Put the pan under the broiler and let the muffins brown lightly on bottom side.
When muffins are lightly browned, take them out of the broiler and turn them cut side up.
On each muffin place 1 slice of cheese and 1 slice of tomato.
Sprinkle a little oregano and just a few drops of oil on each.
Put the muffins back on the tin and put them back under the broiler again for about 8 minutes or until the cheese is melted.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and shortening.
Then add eggs, milk, flour and baking powder, blending as you go.
Mix well.
Fold in frosting mix, blending slowly.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: fluffy pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients, add rest and mix.
Let set a minute until mix fluffs up; if too thick add some more milk.
Cook on hot buttered griddle.
(This is the best pancake mix I've come across yet.)

title: caramel corn
directions: Using medium heat, boil the ingredients for 5 minutes, then add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda and stir.
Place corn in a large flat pan.
Pour the cooked mixture over corn and bake 1 hour at 200°. Stir every 15 minutes (very good).

title: caraway pork chops
directions: Using lightly oiled or greased frying pan or Corning Ware with lid, brown chops well on one side.
Add sliced or large diced onion (or onion flakes later with the water).
Brown chops well on other side with onions.
Add caraway seed (a pinch per chop).
When chops are well browned, add water (up to about 1/3 of chops).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook chops a minimum of 1 1/2 hours on low fire, partly covered.
Turn chops occasionally and stir in onions. Add water as necessary.
When chops break to the fork, they are ready.
Add enough water to make gravy.

title: meatloaf with applesauce
directions: Combine loaf ingredients in bowl and mix together.
Form into a loaf and put in roaster.

title: artichoke spread(extremely delicious, but very high in fat!)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican doughnut strips
directions: Bring water, butter, sugar and salt to boiling.
Add flour all at once, stirring fast.
Cook and stir with wooden spoon until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Remove from heat and cool for 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each until smooth.
Spoon dough into a pastry bag fitted with a large star tip.
Pipe the dough into strips 3 inches long and 3/4 inch wide onto a baking sheet lined with waxed paper.
Freeze strips about 20 minutes.
Do not remove any from freezer until ready to fry.
Fry dough in hot oil 4 to 5 minutes turning occasionally.
Drain on paper towel.

title: crunchy potato chip salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine vinegar and mayonnaise.
Stir in all remaining ingredients, except chips.
Cover and chill.
When ready to serve, add crushed chips and toss lightly.

title: autumn cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and margarine.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers neapolitan
directions: Prepare peppers for stuffing.
Mix stuffing (all ingredients except olive oil and tomato sauce*).
Add more oil if this is dry. Stuff the peppers.
Place stuffed peppers upright in deep baking dish.
Pour oil over peppers and top with 1 tablespoon of tomato sauce for each.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 1 hour.
Serves 4, hot or cold.

title: missy potatoes
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Spoon into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: angel food snowball cake
directions: Mix jello, water and juice; chill until slightly thickened. Add crushed pineapple.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed on package. Save 2 cups for icing if large pan is used.
Add balance of Dream Whip to jello mixture.
Tear cake into bite size pieces. Alternate layers of cake and jello mixture in pan.
Chill overnight and frost with remaining Dream Whip.
If desired, sprinkle coconut on top.
Can use strawberry jello and strawberries or orange jello and mandarin oranges.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix with other ingredients and bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Drain pork and beans before mixing with other ingredients.

title: hamburger goo
directions: Put the beef in the skillet.
Stir and brown over medium heat. Pour off the fat.
Add celery, onion, sugar, vinegar, mustard and ketchup.
Sprinkle the flour on the mixture.
Stir to mix well. Simmer about 20 minutes.
Cut buns in half and put them together with the beef mixture in between.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: cheese blitz
directions: Trim crusts from the bread and roll flat with a rolling pin. Mix first four ingredients and spread each slice with some.
Roll each like a jelly roll and cut into thirds.
Dip each piece into melted butter and then in cinnamon sugar.
Place on a cookie sheet and freeze (this is a must).
They may be stored in baggies in the freezer after they are frozen.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crispy fish batter
directions: Mix together and store in an airtight container.
When ready to make batter into dip, pour amount desired into bowl and add water to desired consistency.
Dip food and fry in hot oil.
Also good for onion rings, chicken, mushrooms, etc.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix with juice of oranges; add cooking oil.
Add well beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Fold in orange slices.
Grease and flour 3 layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook whole chicken in 1-quart water until tender.
Remove meat from bone.
To broth and meat add 4 cups water and rest of the ingredients.
Cook until vegetables and noodles are tender.

title: key lime pie
directions: Pour in baked crust.
Top with meringue.

title: cream cheese brownie pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and one egg.
Beat until smooth.
Combine brownie mix, oil, water and 2 eggs and mix well. Spread half of brownie mix in crust.
Spoon cheese mix over brownie layer.
Top with remaining brownie mix.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: sunday night scramble
directions: Beat eggs and sour cream until light and fluffy.
Stir in cheese and onions.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add curry powder and stir for a few seconds.
Add eggs.
Lower heat and stir gently until eggs are cooked to desired consistency.

title: taco soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat thoroughly.
You may add water, if too thick.

title: deviled crab - williamsburg style
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Remove 2 tablespoons margarine and mix with bread crumbs; set aside.
To remaining margarine, add chopped onion.
Saute until tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in cream and sherry.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in crab, eggs and parsley.
Turn mixture into individual scallop shells or casseroles or a 9-inch baking dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Add onion; cook, covered, on low heat until tender, about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Blend in flour.
Add water, potatoes and salt, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; simmer for about 30 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Add cream; stir well.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine 1/3 c. water, sugar, vinegar and soy sauce. Heat to boiling. Stir in tomatoes, bay leaf and onion. Return to boiling, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat. Simmer 5 minutes.

title: walnut cake
directions: Cream sugar; add egg yolks, vanilla, whiskey, cinnamon, nuts and bread crumbs; add beaten egg whites.
Fold soda in lemon juice; bake in greased pan 40 minutes at 350°.

title: choose a flavor float
directions: Add 1/2 ice cream to a chilled 12-ounce glass.
Add enough carbonated beverage to half fill the glass; stir gently.
Add remaining ice cream.
Fill the glass with remaining carbonated beverage.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Cook 2 hours over low heat.
Stir occasionally.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: witches brew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: sherried fresh tomatoes
directions: Core tomato and slice in half.
Place cut side up on cookie sheet.
Pierce each tomato several times with a fork.
Sprinkle each half with sherry, dill and pepper.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes. (May be prepared to this point 1 hour before serving.)
Top each half with a mixture of mayonnaise and cheese.
Broil for 2 to 3 minutes or until bubbly and slightly browned.
Serve immediately.

title: copper carrots
directions: Peel and slice (in rounds) carrots and boil until tender, approximately 5 minutes.
Cool.
Slice green pepper and onion. Blend together soup, oil, sugar and vinegar.
Add optional ingredients to taste.
Alternate layers of carrots, onion and green pepper. Pour marinade over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.

title: spinach and dill rice(from "vegetarian epicure ii")
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet and add fresh spinach (or thawed frozen spinach).
Add garlic, salt or soy sauce, pepper dill weed and vinegar.
Cook over medium heat about 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add the cooked rice and toss until well blended.
Cover and leave over low heat for 3 or 4 minutes.
Toss together the 2 cups of cheeses.
Sprinkle over rice mixture when served.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, green pepper, onion and carrots into colander, sprinkling layers with salt.
Let drain at room temperature for 4 hours; press to remove remaining moisture.
Combine vinegar, water and sugar in bowl; mix well.
Combine with cabbage mixture in serving bowl; mix well.
Marinate in refrigerator for 12 hours or longer.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: one minute fudge
directions: Blend the cream cheese and sugar together (hands work best!). In a larger bowl, melt chocolate chips in microwave.
Add cheese and sugar mixture to chocolate chips.
Add nuts (optional). Spread on buttered pan/sheet and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Makes 2 pounds of fudge.

title: chili cheese cornbread
directions: Sprinkle onion in 1 1/2-quart round glass baking dish (a 1 1/2-quart glass ring mold may be used instead.
Baking time is the same).
Top with bacon slices, cover with paper towel.
Microwave on High 5 minutes, or until bacon is crisp, rotating quarter turn every 2 minutes.
Remove bacon strips to paper towel.
With slotted spoon, remove onion and set aside.
Pour bacon drippings into measuring cup, adding oil if necessary to make 1/4 cup.

title: pizza dip
directions: Set cream cheese out and let warm.
Spread into pizza dish until evenly spread out (moistened fingers work well), then pour on chili sauce and spread evenly.
Spread chopped or ground up pepperoni or meat of choice.
Sprinkle chopped up green pepper evenly and sprinkle green onions (using some of green top) evenly. Save a few green onions and green peppers to garnish top.
Spread Mozzarella cheese over top.
Garnish with green pepper, onions and chopped or sliced black olives.
Sprinkle with ground paprika for color.
(Green olives are good, too.)
Try your own variations.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in defatted chicken broth. Combine soup, milk and garlic powder.
Add beans, sauteed onions, celery, mushrooms and water chestnuts to soup mixture.
Pour into a lightly greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cornflake crumbs or low-fat cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: pennsylvania fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and milk.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Take off burner.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until it starts to thicken.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Peanut butter may be added after taking fudge off burner.

title: short 'n sweet peach crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place peaches in greased shallow 1 quart baking dish.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg; mix with fork and spread over peaches.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: snacks
directions: Mix all the cereals, pretzels and peanuts together in a large roaster.
Melt bacon fat and butter together and mix other seasonings.
Pour seasoned fat over the dry cereal and toss to mix the seasoning.
Bake in 200° oven for one hour.
Turn occasionally during the one hour so seasoning will be equally distributed. Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: lemonilla ring cake
directions: Combine the ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Beat for 10 minutes at medium speed.
Pour the batter into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done when tested.
Let cool, then remove from the pan. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: crumbly soap
directions: Mix water, fat, ammonia,
borax, sugar and lye in order given in a plastic pail.	Sprinkle
lye in last.	Stir and let set 5 to 10 minutes,
then
stir
again.
Stir
frequently the first hour and half.
There
after
every
hour throughout the day.
Make sure there is no liquid in the bottom at the end of the day.
(If there is, you may stir it several times the next morning.) After it is all done, let it set in pail a few days, then cover soap or put
in
tight
container to prevent drying out.
The
mixture may
look
separate at first.
But it will eventually absorb
and look beautiful and crumbly by stirring. For best results make only one batch at a time or use separate container for each batch.

title: micro apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Put in microwave-safe dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Mix remaining ingredients and crumble over apples. Microwave 5 to 10 minutes depending on your oven.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Mix thoroughly and put in a 9 x 13-inch dish; freeze.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix stick of oleo, cream cheese and flour well.
Form into 24 balls about size of walnut.
Press into 24 small tart tins.
Fill with the following: chopped pecans pieces (3 to 4 pieces in each section).
In separate bowl, mix 2 eggs (beaten), brown sugar, vanilla, pinch of salt and melted butter.
Pour over nut pieces to 1/4-inch from top.
Place broken nut pieces on top of each tart. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool before removing from pan.
These are great to freeze also.

title: bread pudding
directions: Warm milk and honey together.
Prepare bread cubes, removing crusts.
Place in 2-quart buttered casserole.
Beat eggs slightly with salt.
Add to bread cubes with honey mixture and vanilla. Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Heat oven to 300°.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes (or until custard tests done near center).
May be served warm or cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: wonder salad
directions: Drain and mix first 5 ingredients.
Dissolve salt and sugar in vinegar; pour over bean mixture.
Marinate overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Pour in greased long bread pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale to fill punch bowl.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
The pan should be sprayed with Pam first.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Frost while warm.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Blend tuna, celery, onion, eggs and mayonnaise.
Cut tops from tomatoes; scoop out seeds.
Stuff with tuna mixture.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; cover blender.
Blend for 30 seconds.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Beat together all ingredients, except egg whites.
Beat whites until stiff
and
mix in batter.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° until firm to touch.

title: herb fried chicken
directions: In food processor or blender, combine flour, oats, spices and herbs.
Process slightly.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites and beer until foamy, place in shallow dish.
Dip chicken in egg mixture and then roll in flour mixture.
Fry in oil.
Remaining flour mixture may be used to make milk gravy and served with chicken.
Delicious!

title: chinese chews
directions: Spread in thin sheet.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cut in squares while hot.
Form into balls by rolling each square in palm of hand. Roll in granulated sugar.
Makes 24 chews.

title: wisconsin broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in 4 tablespoons of butter until soft.
Stir in flour.
Add water and cook over low heat until thick.
Blend in cheese.
Combine sauce and thawed, well drained broccoli.
Add eggs and mix gently.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs and dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs; stir in oil, zucchini, sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon together. Stir the flour mixture into the egg mixture until well blended. Add raisins and nuts; mix well.
Pour out into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 55 minutes.

title: bill boland's onion rings
directions: Slice onions into rings 1/4 to 1/8-inch thick.
Keep rings dry.
Mix egg and milk; sift together dry ingredients.
Gradually add egg mixture; beat until smooth.
Add butter.
Heat fat to 360°.
Drop battered onion rings into fat, one at a time.
Don't fry too many rings at one time.
Fry until brown, turning once. Drain on absorbent paper.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Pour boiling water over Jell-O.
Mix well; add juice from pineapple.
Cool to room temperature; then put in refrigerator until firm.
Whip until fluffy.
Fold in sour cream, pineapple and walnuts.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate icing for cakes
directions: Stir first three ingredients together well, boil 2 minutes. Add the chocolate chips and marshmallows.

title: easy chicken pasta
directions: In skillet brown chicken in hot oil. Set aside. Add soup, water and vegetables in a saucepan. Heat to a boil. Add uncooked pasta. Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring often. The pasta cooks in the soup. Add browned chicken. Cook 5 minutes more or until pasta is done, stirring often. Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: crab muffins
directions: Slightly soften butter and cheese for ease in mixing.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread on muffin halves.
Place on cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, then switch to broil for about 1 to 2 minutes more.

title: impossible pineapple pie
directions: Blend for 5 minutes and pour into 10-inch greased deep pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hickory smoked barbecue pork sandwiches
directions: Brush pork on both sides with mixture of liquid smoke and water.
Arrange on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Roast in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, until cooked through.
Heat barbecue sauce.
Slice pork; arrange on rolls, spooning warm sauce over and top with your favorite cole slaw.
Garnish with pickle chips and parsley sprigs.
Serves 6.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Toss together with 8 ounces low calorie or regular Italian dressing.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil
sugar,
water, margarine, corn syrup and cinnamon down into
a
syrup.
Boil
sweet
potatoes until tender with peeling. When
tender, peel and slice.
Put into Corning Ware dish
and pour
syrup over potatoes.	Place in center of rack and
cook until
desired.
Take
from oven and pour miniature marshmallows over potatoes; let melt.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Crumble the Blue cheese and blend all ingredients; keep refrigerated.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix mustard and jelly on top of stove in saucepan until it dissolves.
Drop hot dogs in and cook on low heat until wieners are done.

title: pork apritada
directions: Slice pork into individual pieces.
Saute in garlic, onions and tomatoes.
Season with salt.
Add vinegar and let boil for 5 minutes, then add enough water or stock to make meat tender and make up for sauce.
When almost done, add sliced pepper and thicken with bread crumbs.
Cook for 5 minutes thereafter.
Remove from fire and garnish with fried potatoes.

title: tropical pudding
directions: Mix juice into pudding with wire whisk.
Stir in yogurt and coconut extract.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill 30 minutes before serving.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put into oblong casserole dish. Then layer next 3 ingredients on top.
Top with grated cheese and serve with corn chips.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut the tops off the green peppers; remove seeds.
Cook peppers in boiling water for 3 to 4 minutes; drain.
Coat a nonstick skillet with vegetable oil spray.
Cook turkey and onion until turkey is done and onion is soft.
Add tomatoes.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients except bread crumbs. Stuff peppers with turkey mixture.
(These can be frozen at this point.)
To bake, place in a shallow baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Bring pineapple juice and water to a boil.
Add gelatin.
Stir in pie filling and cola.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sour cream.
On a large tray, layer in this order:
lettuce, tomatoes, cream cheese/sour cream mixture, olives, Cheddar cheese and salsa. Grab a chip and dip.

title: cheese sauce for broccoli
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk and bouillon cubes.
Stir over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil. Add a little of the heated sauce to eggs.
Stir this into rest of sauce.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add mushrooms; pour over broccoli in a casserole.
Sprinkle with almonds and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients and let set in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: country kitchen casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into 2-quart baking dish. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain.
Mix all other ingredients together. Spoon into lightly greased casserole.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grape salad
directions: Cook the salt, lemon juice, pineapple juice, cherry juice, flour and vinegar. Cool. Whip 1 pint cream and fold into cooled mixture. Combine marshmallows, grapes, pineapple, cherries and nuts. Carefully fold into fruit mixture the cooked mixture. Refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Mix well; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally until mixture reaches 285°.
Remove from heat at once; stir in nuts and butter.
Cook, stirring constantly, until it reaches 295°.
Remove; add vanilla and baking soda.
Stir to blend.
Pour onto well-buttered sheet.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, shortening, butter, egg yolk and vanilla (mixer okay).
Mix in by hand the flour and salt until dough holds together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Beat egg white slightly.
Dip ball in egg white and then in nuts.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press thumb into center. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Put Kisses on when hot or, when cool, fill with preserves.
Refrigerate if filled with preserves.

title: tomato hors 'doeuvres
directions: Wash and dry tomatoes.
Take the cores out and make a hole in the tomatoes.
Fry the bacon crisp; drain and crumble.
Add the Tabasco sauce, about 1/4 teaspoon should do.
Stuff the tomatoes. Stick each tomato with a toothpick and arrange on a platter with a few stems of fresh parsley for color.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In large saucepan with heavy bottom, mix all ingredients until well blended.
Cook over medium heat for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 6 cups of sauce.

title: mallow fudge(microwave candy)
directions: In microwave bowl combine milk, butter, and sugar.
Microwave on high 9-12 minutes or until soft ball forms when small amount is dropped in cold water, stir every 3 minutes.
Remove cover from marshmallow creme, microwave in jar on 50% for 30 seconds or until soft.
Stir into sugar mixture with chocolate chips and nuts until well blended.
Pour into medium pan 8 X 10 inch.
Let stand or refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: coconut sugar cookies(a tender, buttery sugar cookie)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, butter, coconut and vanilla in large mixing
bowl.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Roll in sugar and place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with bottom of glass.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are delicately browned.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet to cooling rack. Yield: 4 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside. In a large bowl, cream the butter, sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Put in greased 8 x 6-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: watergate cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Bake about 45 minutes at 375° until no imprint remains.
Ice cake.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Use the washed broccoli flowerets and the stems, peeled.
Mix all ingredients and toss lightly.
Keep refrigerated until serving time.

title: pineapple dressing
directions: Grease 9 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Beat eggs.
Mix sugar and flour and add to eggs.
Add pineapple and juice to egg mixture and place in dish.
Break bread in small pieces and place on top. Cover with pieces of sliced margarine.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: tater tot and hamburger soup casserole
directions: Spread meat on bottom of glass casserole dish.
Add soup and spread out.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: company chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, drained pineapple (reserve juice), grapes, celery and peanuts.
Taste for salt (salted nuts will probably furnish enough).
Stir in tarragon.

title: hot shrimp salad
directions: Drain orange and grapefruit sections, reserving 1/3 cup of the juice.
Set juice aside.

title: cranberry orange nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease one large loaf pan (9 1/4 x 5 1/4-inches).
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Combine orange juice, butter and eggs; stir into dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Spoon mixture into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.

title: gazpacho
directions: Into blender put the first four ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour into large plastic bowl.
Add broth, vinegar, olive oil, salt, pepper and Tabasco to taste.
Stir well.
Now add the remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight or at least 4 hours; stir again before serving.
This improves with age.
Serves 8.

title: mustard barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1-quart glass measure. Stir well. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes, stirring with a wire whisk after 3 minutes. Serve with pork or beef. Yields 1 1/3 cups (about 15 calories per tablespoon).

title: beef and cabbage taco casserole
directions: In a large bowl toss potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese, 1/8 teaspoon onion salt and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper. Press into bottom and up the sides of greased 1 quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orzo salad(rice shaped pasta)
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Omit any salt, drain the tomatoes and reserve 1 teaspoon of the oil.
Chop 2 tablespoons tomatoes.
Save the rest for another use.
Combine orzo, tomatoes, red pepper, green onions, parsley and olives; toss lightly.

title: grandma simon's mexican chicken soup
directions: In a large pot, simmer chicken, sliced onion, salt and pepper for 2 hours, until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth. Strain broth and cool chicken.
Cut up chicken into bite sizes, discarding skin and bones.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.	Place selected fruit in dish. Mix flour,	sugar
and
milk
together.
Pour on top of fruit. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: dutch oven - enchilada casserole
directions: Brown together ground beef, salt and chopped onion.
Add tomato soup, enchilada sauce and water and simmer.
Remove 3/4 of meat mixture from the pan.
Place over top of remaining mixture 3 corn tortillas (uncooked).
Add layer of meat. Put 1/4 pound grated cheese on top.
Add layer of meat.
Put 3 corn tortillas on top.
Add another layer of meat.
Add 1/4 pound of cheese.
Place lid on pan and let simmer.
Makes 6 portions.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Start oven at 375°.
Grease a 5 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Soak bread in water; chop onion and parsley fine.
Mash soaked bread with fork; add meat and rest of ingredients, except butter, tomato sauce and oregano.
Mix well and place in pan; shape into a loaf. Dot with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce over meat; sprinkle with oregano and bake 20 minutes more.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften ingredients.
Blend and add cut-up shrimp.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in baking dish. Crumble crackers or potato chips on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cracker salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend well.
Store, covered, overnight in refrigerator.

title: baker's german's sweet chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with oleo over low heat; gradually blend in milk.
Mix sugar, flour and salt; beat in eggs and vanilla gradually.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into shell.
Mix coconut and pecans and sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until top is puffed.
Cool at least 4 hours before serving.

title: mom's chocolate gravy
directions: Heat milk to a simmer.
In a bowl, mix together sugar, flour and cocoa.
Stir into milk, mixing well.
Use a whip to remove the lumps.
Stir constantly until gravy thickens; add butter and vanilla.
Serve over biscuits or toast.

title: kraut
directions: Put water in large kettle and bring to a boil.
Pack cabbage in hot jars.
Add salt, sugar and vinegar to each packed jar of cabbage.
Pour hot water over packed jars.
Don't pack too tight!
Take air bubbles out by running a table knife around inside of jar after you pour hot water in packed jars.
Clean top of jar well.
Seal.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Flour a clean surface.
Pour batter on floured surface and a little flour at a time on batter.
Knead well; let rise double in bulk.
Oil or grease a pan.
Make into rolls; let rise double in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 10 or 15 minutes, until brown as you like.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Bring margarine, water and cocoa to a boil.
Mix dry ingredients; pour cocoa mixture over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs, and vanilla.
Pour into large 11 inch x 17 inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Remove skin from potatoes and mash. Cook bacon until crisp; crumble. Discard all but 1/2 teaspoon drippings in pan. Chop celery and onions. Add chicken broth, milk, mashed potatoes, celery, onions, garlic, salt and pepper to drippings in pan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Simmer 10 minutes. Stir in sour cream and bacon. Ladle soup into bowls and shred cheese on top.

title: easy custard pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla and salt.
Mix in can of milk.
Sprinkle grated nutmeg on top.
Pour in well-greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: best banana bread
directions: Put all ingredients except nuts in large bowl and beat well. Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Toothpick inserted in middle of loaf will come out clean when bread is done.
Cool and store overnight before cutting.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: lemony angel cake
directions: To make filling:
At least 1 hour before using, beat pudding mix and milk according to package directions.
Fold in lemon yogurt until blended.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour, until mixture is of spreading consistency.

title: peanut butter and jelly cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix about half of the cake mix (dry), peanut butter, butter, water and eggs in a large bowl until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in peanuts.
Place about 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press thumb deeply in center of each ball.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Fill thumbprints with jelly.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 12-inch cake pan by directions on box.
Cook in 350° oven until done.
Punch holes in cake and let cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cake.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over rice and herbs. Place rice in a 2-quart casserole. Add soup, mushrooms with liquid, water and seasonings. Mix and let stand. Saut onions in oil until glossy and add to casserole. Brown meat in frying pan and add to rice mixture. Can refrigerate overnight. When ready to bake, two hours at 325°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch and add water.
Cook until transparent; add Jell-O and red food coloring.
Let cool.
Pour over fresh berries in pie shell.
Put Cool Whip on when ready to eat.
Delicious!!!

title: date bars
directions: Mix first five ingredients until it is a crumb mixture.
Cook dates, water and sugar until thick.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan spread 3/4 of crumb mixture; pat down.
Spread date filling on top.
Sprinkle rest of crumb mixture on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: In medium bowl, combine chicken, 1 cup cheese, chilies and onion.
In bottom of 3-quart oblong baking dish, spread 1/2 can enchilada sauce; set aside.

title: patricia hawkins liston's sopa de fideo(one dish meal)
directions: Preheat electric skillet to 300°.
Melt shortening.
Break vermicelli into small pieces and saute until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Add beef and cook until meat loses red color.
Stir in salt, pepper, garlic salt, onion, celery, green pepper and drained corn.
Add tomatoes and water.
Stir gently. Set temperature at 200°, with the vent closed.
Cook 35 minutes. Place slices of cheese on top.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 4.
May be doubled easily.

title: chocolate marshmallow pie
directions: Melt and stir the marshmallows and chocolate bars until smooth.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour into a baked pie shell, graham cracker crust or chocolate crumb crust.
Refrigerate.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries, oranges, and lemon, mix well and add sugar. Mix again and store in refrigator.

title: tamale
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add 1/2 of catsup and 1/2 of grated cheese.
Add all other ingredients. Put in large Pyrex bowl and bake at 300° about 1 hour.
Top with remaining catsup and cheese.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cut peppers into thin strips.
Cook with sliced celery in margarine for 2 minutes.
Add chicken broth.
Blend cornstarch with cold water and soy sauce.
Gradually stir into broth.
Add onion soup mix.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles. Add chicken, mushrooms and bean sprouts.
Heat.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: oatmeal cookies(diabetic cookie)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Measure oatmeal into bowl.
Stir in melted margarine and mix well.
Stir in eggs and sweetener, then add flour, baking powder and salt, alternating with the combined milk and vanilla.
Add raisins.
Drop onto cookie sheet from level teaspoon and bake until golden brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Cook and stir onions and green pepper in butter until onions are tender.
Add clams, cheese, catsup and Worcestershire sauce; cook, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: stuffed chicken breasts(serves 4)
directions: Mix toasted wheat germ, onion, basil and garlic powder into melted butter.
Combine stock base and flour; gradually add wine and half and half.
Stir until smooth.
Add 1 tablespoon of this sauce to wheat germ mixture and set remainder aside.
Place chicken breast on a board, cover with waxed paper and flatten with a mallet.
Place equal amount of wheat germ stuffing in center of each chicken breast.
Roll breasts around stuffing.
Fasten with picks.
Brown chicken and place in a baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and whipped condensed milk; set aside. Prepare Dream Whip according to package.
Fold in whipped condensed milk mixture, fold in blueberries.
Pour into crumb crust, chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add flour, sugar and salt; mix together.
Put into 8-inch pie crust.
Dot with butter.
Place top crust on and crimp edges.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine corn syrup and sugar in saucepan. Heat until mixture begins to boil, stirring frequently. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter until mixture is smooth. Put corn flakes in large bowl. Pour mixture over flakes and stir. Let cool. Roll into balls.

title: dee's seven layer casserole
directions: Layer in a casserole dish ingredients in above order.
Salt and pepper each layer to taste.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350° to 375°.

title: rice krispie balls
directions: Stick toothpicks into marshmallows and place them into freezer while preparing sauce.
In double boiler, melt caramels, butter and Eagle Brand milk.
Dip marshmallows into sauce and roll into Rice Krispies.

title: louisiana shrimp bake
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine.
Blend in flour and salt and cook until bubbly.
Stir in tomatoes, shrimp and sherry.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer covered for 10 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup cheese, eggs and rice.
Pour in 2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25-35 minutes or microwave for 5-7 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill 1 hour.
Serve with your favorite finger vegetables.

title: tang pie(makes two pies)
directions: Mix milk, Tang and sour cream.
Pour into pie crusts.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pies.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump fruit into greased cake pan.
Crumble dry cake mix over fruit.
Cover top completely with butter.
Nuts, raisins, coconut, etc. may be added to fruit.
Serve as a cobbler with cream, whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place shredded cabbage in a 4-quart casserole.
Pour milk over, sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with margarine.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake another 30 minutes, until bread is brown and cabbage is tender.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add taco seasoning.
In a casserole dish, layer as follows:
meat, beans (do not drain), rice (do not drain) and cheese.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: pat's potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add Miracle Whip if needed.
Save 1 egg.
Slice and garnish top. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: my best gingerbread
directions: Combine sugar, wine, water, cloves, cinnamon and lemon in a saucepan large enough to hold plums.
Bring ingredients to a boil and cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add plums and bring mixture to a boil; lower heat and simmer the plums for 10 to 20 minutes, depending on their ripeness, until they are tender but still hold their shape.
Some plums will be cooked before others.
Remove cooked fruit.
Then, when all are cooked, return all the plums to the syrup.

title: easy custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In medium bowl, combine condensed milk, water, salt and vanilla.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 10 minutes; reduce heat to 300° and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool coconut.
Add 1 cup coconut to filling.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix melted oleo, rice, salt and onion flakes.
Stir in soup and water; mix.
Place in baking dish.
Arrange chicken on top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: golf balls
directions: Mix all ingredients but wax and chips and roll in little balls.
Melt in double boiler, paraffin wax and chocolate chips. Dip balls in chocolate.

title: melt-in-your-mouth chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken; take off bone and cut into pieces. Place in 9 x 13 bowl or pan. Spread Veg-All on top of chicken. In pan, mix and bring to boil 2 cups of chicken broth and soup. Pour over Veg-All and chicken.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until top is golden.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: "heavenly" fruit salad
directions: Cut Mandarin orange in half.
Cut whole strawberries in quarters.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: grape pie
directions: Slip skins from grapes.
Heat pulp to boiling; simmer a few minutes.
Press through sieve to remove seeds.
Add skins and sugar, mixed with flour, salt and lemon peel.
Fill 9-inch pastry-lined pan.
Distribute butter over grapes.
Adjust top crust on pie; seal and flute edge.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pineapple torte
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, rum flavoring, water and oil in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of mixer for 2 minutes.
Stir in 2/3 cup of the coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool on rack.
Cut into three 10 x 5-inch pieces. Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup of the juice.
Combine pudding mix, 3/4 cup of the pineapple and reserved juice; stir to blend. Fold in whipped topping.
Place 1 cake layer on plate; spread with some of the topping mixture.
Top with half the remaining pineapple.
Repeat layers, ending with cake.
Frost cake with remaining topping mixture.
Cover with rest of coconut.

title: fried rice
directions: Brown bacon and add diced vegetables.
Boil your rice.
Add rice to cooked vegetables, then add soy sauce to taste.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Put short ribs in soup pot.
Cover ribs with water.
Bring to boil (do not skim top).
Reduce heat and add remaining ingredients.
Cover with lid and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Cook barley separately.
Drain. Cool, then add to soup.

title: vegetable lasagne
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Line bottom of large baking dish with noodles.
Add a layer of Mozzarella cheese, then add a layer of cottage cheese mixture,* then add a layer of spaghetti sauce.
Repeat and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on large ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well.
Set aside.
Saute onion, celery and pepper in margarine until tender. Mix together the soup, cheese, garlic powder and 3/4 cup stuffing mix.
Stir in onion mixture and spinach.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over top and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: easy bean dip(low-fat, too!)
directions: Mix beans and onion together.
Add salsa and cheese to your liking.
Bake in small casserole dish at 350° until heated.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: corn bread stuffed squash
directions: Wash squash well; cover with cold water.
Bring to boil and boil rapidly for 20 minutes, or until squash is tender.
Mix all other ingredients.
Cut squash in the center the long way.
Scoop out seeds and pulp; add to bread crumb mixture.
Salt and pepper squash shells lightly.
Stuff with bread crumb stuffing; place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: rice
directions: Fry rice in cooking oil until brown. Add chopped onion and green pepper. Fry about 1 minute.

Grind cumin and garlic in a spice grinder. Add ground spices, tomato sauce and chicken broth along with 2 1/2 cups boiling water. When all is boiling, cover and lower heat to simmer. Do not stir after this point. Cook until tender. Add peas for color.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburg, green pepper and onion together and drain.
Put into casserole.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 450°, covered.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in unbaked pie shell.

title: plum pudding
directions: Combine suet, boiling water, brown sugar, molasses, soda, salt and enough flour to mix together.
Add raisins, citron, currants, lemon peel and allspice.
Place in greased 1-pound coffee cans. Steam over boiling water for about 1 hour.
Test with a toothpick. Serve with hard sauce.

title: grandma's coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees and grease a 9 x 13 cake pan.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put first four ingredients in refrigerator overnight.
Just before serving toss with Miracle Whip, sugar (Equal) and vinegar.

title: low-fat chicken pot pie
directions: Saute carrots, celery and onion in small amount of chicken gravy; mix with chicken, remaining vegetables, seasonings and enough gravy to fill bottom of pie crust.
Put top crust on and tuck edges under and flute.
Cut steam holes.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned and inside mixture is bubbly.
Heat any leftover gravy on low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbling.
Spoon over pieces of pie.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Better if made the night before.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken by boiling.
When done, cut into pieces and put in casserole dish.
Prepare stuffing mix as directed.
When done, add rice to it and put it all in the casserole dish with chicken. Add pimentos; mix.
Pour mushroom soup over and mix a little.
Put cover on and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in salt water.
Peel and slice in large bowl. Dice celery and onion in with potatoes.
Slice bacon and fry bacon until crisp.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain and add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Combine ham and broccoli.
Put a layer of cracker crumbs in the bottom of greased casserole.
Place broccoli on top. Pour soup, water and 1/2 stick melted butter over.
Place 1/2 pound sliced Velveeta cheese on top and a thin layer of cracker crumbs. Pour 1/4 stick butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain completely. Add soups and water, and bring to a hard boil. Remove from heat. Add sour cream; stir completely. Boil egg noodles while browning meat. Drain and add hamburger mixture, stir. Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: buttered rum-nut rolls
directions: Combine 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/4 cup butter, milk, flour and 1/2 teaspoon rum extract.
Cook over low heat until mixture boils. Pour into a lightly greased 10 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle pecans over sugar mixture.
Roll dough on a lightly floured surface to measure a 14 x 12-inch rectangle.
Brush dough with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Mix remaining brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon rum extract.
Sprinkle over dough.
Roll dough tightly in a jellyroll fashion, beginning at the long side, being careful to keep to 14-inch in length.
Cut roll into 12 slices.
Place in prepared pan.
Brush top with remaining butter.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts, 45 minutes or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn rolls onto serving tray immediately.
Yields 12 rolls.

title: janey's chocolate passion dessert
directions: Cut brownies in to 1/2-inch cubes.
Layer in a 3-quart serving bowl: 1/2 of the brownies, 1 cup of the strawberries, 1 sliced banana and 1 tub of the Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 16 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine undrained pineapple with dry pudding.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Mix until well blended.
Add nuts and/or coconut, if desired.

title: salsa
directions: Peel, core and chop tomatoes.
In a 6 to 8 quart pan, combine ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; boil gently, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into hot jars, leaving headspace at the top.
Wipe jar tops and threads clean.
Place hot lids on jars; screw bands on firmly.
Process in boiling water canner 15 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 pint jars of salsa.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Add other ingredients except cheese. Pour in casserole and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cupcakes
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and peanut butter.
Add vanilla and eggs, beating well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk to the mixture.
Bake in tins lined with bake cups for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese or chocolate frosting.
Makes about 2 dozen cupcakes.

title: cranberry-chili meatballs
directions: Mix well.
You may need a little milk to mix ingredients together well.
Form into 1 1/2 to 2-inch meatballs and place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lace cookies
directions: Combine oats, sugar, flour and salt; mix well.	Stir in remaining
ingredients.
Drop
by teaspoon (1/2 full) 3-inches apart onto aluminum foil lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to	8
minutes
or	until edges are brown.	Cool completely before removing from cookie sheet.
Yield:
6 1/2 dozen.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Mix
Cool
Whip,
sour cream and cottage cheese.
Drain fruit cocktail
and add to mixture.
Nuts may be added. Chill for at least 2 hours.

title: baked meatball dish
directions: Combine.
Pour this mixture over meatballs.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: You must beat for 15 minutes.
When crust has cooled, top with above filling, then top with 3 sliced bananas.
Spread over the bananas, 1 large can crushed pineapple (drained).
Then cover with Cool Whip.

title: raisin casserole bread
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine and cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle or crumble in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm milk mixture, egg and 3 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Cover; let rise in warm place, free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Stir batter down.
Beat in raisins.
Turn into 2 greased 1-quart casseroles.
Round bakeproof bowls are fine.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fettucine alfredo for 2
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
Return noodles to saucepan, or put in warm chafing dish or electric skillet to finish at the table.
Fold in butter until melted.
Pour in whipping cream and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Fold and stir until cream is partially absorbed and cheese is melted.
Just before serving, add salt, pepper and nutmeg if desired.
Makes 2 servings.

title: different pie crust
directions: Blend flour, sugar, and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg, blend in vinegar, add cold water.
Sprinkle this over flour and shortening mixture, a tablespoon at a time.
Toss with fork to mix.
Roll on floured surface.
Bake at 400 degrees.

title: candied flowers for decorations on cakes
directions: You will need 1 small paint brush and 1 baking rack covered with wax paper.

title: muffuletta(in a bun)
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients on bottom half of bun; top with remaining bun half and wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until sandwich is thoroughly heated.
Makes 1 serving.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs, oleo and milk until well blended. Stir in bread crumbs.
Add pineapple.
Pour in greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hands.
Put in casserole dish.
Spread catsup over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cherry delight
directions: Crush graham crackers and add 1/4 cup powdered sugar and butter.
Mix and press in bottom of 9x13 dish.
Whip the lucky whip, vanilla and milk.
Add cream cheese and powdered sugar. Pour mixture on top of crust.
Top with cherry pie filling. Chill and cut into squares.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add peanut butter; beat well.
Gradually beat in milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and add peanuts.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Freeze until firm.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, eggs and half of butter.
Pour into casserole. Spread cracker crumbs on top of mixture.
Pour remaining butter over top of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian kielbasa
directions: Place kielbasa in a 3-quart casserole.
Add the pineapple, salsa and brown sugar.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juices off peaches and pears; cut up into small chunks. Add pineapple chunks with juice to the lemon instant pudding.
Mix in the peaches and pears.
Add the sliced banana just before serving.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Prepare and cook corn; heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons butter until onion is tender. Remove from heat; stir in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir one minute.
Stir in corn and egg.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Combine cracker crumbs and the 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Sprinkle evenly over corn mixture. Bake uncovered 30 to 35 minutes.
(For cheese scalloped corn, fold 1/2 cup shredded natural Cheddar cheese into the sauce mixture.) Serves 4.

title: hamburger vegetable casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Boil vegetables in 1/2 cup water for 10 minutes.
Combine soup, vegetables and hamburger and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Do not drain vegetables.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and egg; beat well.
Add molasses; stir until blended.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Beat well.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets 2-inches apart.
Sprinkle sugar on top, if desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together and pour into ice cream freezer.
Freeze according to instructions on ice cream freezer, usually 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: make your own shake and bake
directions: Mix, then shake and bake.

title: jell0-fruit salad
directions: Mix dry jello with Cool Whip, then add cottage cheese and fruit.
Set in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: colored milk painting(non-eatable)
directions: Pour the condensed milk into small cups.
Add drops of different coloring to each cup.
Allow pictures created with colored milk paint to dry for several hours.

title: hamburger meat and veg-all soup
directions: Brown meat in small amount of shortening.
Add all ingredients to meat and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Can add green pepper, onions or mushrooms.
If added, place on meat before potatoes.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Blend eggs and water; set aside.
Heat oil in wok.
Add green onions; stir-fry for 30 seconds.
Add egg mixture; scramble.
Stir in rice, gently separating grains.
Add shrimp and lite soy sauce; cook, stirring until thoroughly heated.

title: yellow tomato preserves
directions: Prick tomatoes, add sugar, 1 sliced lemon, and juice from 1 lemon. Mix.
Tie mace and ginger in thin cloth bag and add to mix.
Simmer until fruit is transparent.
Remove tomatoes.
Boil syrup until thick.
Add tomatoes, heat to boil.
Either cool and store in refrigerator or can as you would a jam or jelly.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Layer as follows:
avocado, then mix sour cream and taco mix together and spread over.
Add picante sauce over, then cheeses, tomatoes, olives and green onions.
Place in 13 x 9-inch dish and chill for 4 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips or Doritos chips.

title: whipped cream icing
directions: Boil until thick (stirring constantly), the milk and flour. Remove from stove.
Beat until smooth, then cover and refrigerate until cool.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.
Mix shortening, peanut butter and sugars; mix well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir flour mixture and peanut butter mixture together.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls on baking sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: blackberry wine pound cake
directions: Pour over hot cake as soon as it comes out of oven.
Leave in pan about 10 minutes and take out and cool.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: In a glass bowl, mix together the first 4 ingredients. Microwave on High until the mixture begins to boil; continue microwaving for 2 minutes.
Thoroughly stir in baking soda; mixture turns foamy.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Beat 4 egg yolks; add condensed milk and lime juice.
Beat until thick; pour into baked pie crust.

title: strawberry jelly
directions: Cook over low heat until temperature reads 224°.
Put in canning jars.
Freeze strawberries first for 3 days, then thaw out in bag in sink.
Drain juice from bag.
Should be 3 cups only.

title: meat loaf(quantity)
directions: Place beef in a large mixing bowl.
Finely chop onion, green pepper and celery.
Add to meat.
Add all other ingredients.
Add milk last, using enough to make a moist, but formable consistency. Shape into 3 loaves.
Place bacon strip on each and bake about 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Gravy can be made from pan scrapings.

title: mawmaw's pecan cookies
directions: In medium bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk and vanilla; beat until mix is light and fluffy.
Beat in cream of tartar, then stir in flour and pecans.
Drop by heaping 1/2 teaspoonfuls 1-inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300°
until golden, about 20 minutes.
It makes 5 dozen small cookies.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Very good on dark whole wheat bread (trim crusts).
Filling will keep for a week in the refrigerator. Sandwiches may be made ahead and stay crisp and crunchy.

title: rhubarb 'n dumplings (caramel)(microwave quick)
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine 1 1/4 cups water, brown sugar, first 1/4 cup white sugar, cornstarch and 3 tablespoons butter.
Add the sliced rhubarb.
Microcook uncovered on 100% power (High) for 7 to 9 minutes or until mixture is thickened and bubbly, stirring after every minute.
Cover casserole to keep warm.

title: cucumber soup
directions: Dice cucumber.
Place all ingredients into blender.
Blend until smooth. Store in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Toss fruits, celery and nuts together.
In separate bowl, combine last 5 ingredients.
Toss with fruit mixture.
Chill well. Let sit a couple of hours before serving.

title: chicken broccoli skillet
directions: Cook chicken in Miracle Whip about 8 minutes.
Add broccoli and Velveeta cheese.
Heat.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and oleo. Add syrup, beaten eggs and vanilla. Beat until smooth. Stir in pecans and pour in unbaked pie crust. Bake at approximately 275° for 45 minutes.

title: dorothy smith's apple dapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all dry ingredients. Combine all together.
Add pecans last. Bake in greased Bundt pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: blueberry tea bread
directions: About 3 hours before serving or early in day:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray. In large bowl, mix baking powder, salt, 3 cups cake flour and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Reserve 1 tablespoon corn oil spread for crumb topping.
With pastry blender or two knives used scissor-fashion, cut in remaining corn oil spread until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in milk, vanilla extract and egg until flour is just moistened.
Gently stir in blueberries; spoon batter into loaf pan.
Coarsely chop almonds.
In small bowl, with fork, mix almonds, cinnamon, 2 tablespoons cake flour, 2 tablespoons sugar and reserved corn oil spread until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle crumb topping over batter.
Bake loaf 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool loaf in pan on wire rack 10 minutes; remove from pan and finish cooling on wire rack.
Makes 12 servings.

title: fat free pasta sauce
directions: Crush tomatoes; add tomato paste and combine all ingredients in large saucepan.
Simmer uncovered for 45 minutes or until tender.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: biscontti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toast almonds about 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
In a large bowl, measure 1 1/2 cups flour and add next 7 ingredients.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until just mixed.
Beat mixture 3 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in remaining flour.
Wrap dough with plastic wrap and refrigerate 1 hour or freeze 30 minutes.
Grease large cookie sheet.
Divide dough in half on well floured surface.
Shape each half into a 10 x 3-inch loaf.
Place both halves 2-inches apart.
Bake 25 minutes. Remove from oven and with serrated knife, cut loaves into 3/4-inch slices.
Lay slices on same cookie sheet.
Bake for 5 more minutes. When cooled, cookies can be dipped in or drizzled with melted chocolate, if desired.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.
Contains 125 calories and 3 g. fat each (without chocolate).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix crackers, oleo and poppy seed; save 1 cup.
Put the rest in bottom of long Pyrex dish (line dish well).
On top of mixture, put the deboned chicken, mixed with the sour cream.
Top with the cup of cracker mix.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 50 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Spray Pam on bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Spread crescent roll dough on bottom of dish. Spread sausage or ham over the dough.
Mix eggs, milk, bell pepper, mushrooms and Cheddar cheese together and pour on top of sausage or ham.
Then pour melted margarine on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Will serve 8 to 10 people.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and butter, stirring well. Line 1 3/4-inch muffin pans with miniature paper liners.
Spoon 1 teaspoon of crumb mixture into each liner; gently press into bottom.
Beat cream cheese at high speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating well.
Spoon mixture into liners.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: shrimp dip(serves approximately 15)
directions: Drain the shrimp and rinse.
Soften butter.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thin.
Put in quart container that has a tight seal (Tupperware).
Add onion.
Mix liquid and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add other ingredients.
Seal and store in refrigerator.
Keeps indefinitely.
No cooking.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Blend eggs, oil, sugar and zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to first mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in two greased loaf pans or one greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°. Invert and cool completely before removing from pans.

title: creamy fry baked chicken breasts
directions: Fry chicken until almost done; drain.
Place in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and wine, stirring well.
Spoon sauce evenly over chicken; sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: sausage macaroni casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add green pepper, onion, oregano and pepper.
Stir in tomato sauce and 1/2 cup of water.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add macaroni and 2 tablespoons of cheese.
Mix well. Spoon into 1 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Place the green peppers and hot peppers in a blender container.
Add a small amount of vinegar and blend well.
Pour this mixture into a large saucepan and add the sugar and remaining vinegar.
Bring it to a rolling boil over medium heat and add the liquid pectin; stir for 1 minute.
Bring to a boil again and boil for 1 minute.
Skim any foam from the jelly and add the food coloring.
Pour it into hot, sterilized jelly jars and seal.
This makes about 4 1/2 pints.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix eggs that have been beaten well, butter, syrup and sugar. In separate bowl mix ginger, soda and cinnamon together.
Pour in liquid.
Add flour and water.
Add more water, if needed.
Bake in a greased cake pan at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Lightly cook and drain broccoli.
Combine all ingredients. Pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Combine jello, marshmallows, cream cheese and water in top of double boiler.
Cook until marshmallows melt and cream cheese softens.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients.
Chill.

title: corn casserole
directions: Stir muffin mix into melted butter; add remaining ingredients. Place in greased shallow baking dish. Bake at 350° about 35 minutes. Top with cheese during last 5 minutes of baking time.

title: velvet hammer
directions: Combine all ingredients and float cherries on top.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, apples, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt, soda and nuts.
Mix and bake in greased and floured loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Soften onion in butter in skillet.
Cook zucchini in the water and bouillon until soft.
Put all ingredients in blender and blend.
Delicious!

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add 1 pound cut up chicken breast. Fry until lightly browned.
Cook next 6 ingredients in saucepan. Bring to boil, then add chopped peppers and carrots and cook a minute or two.
Add chicken and serve over hot rice.

title: aunt alice's pound cake
directions: Separate eggs; whip egg whites.
Add 6 level tablespoons sugar while beating.
Place this mixture in refrigerator until rest of cake is mixed.
Cream butter; add gradually the remaining sugar and whip until light.
Add egg yolks about 2 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and cream alternately.
Whip until mixture is light as possible (use low speed on electric mixer).
With mixer still at low speed, whip in the egg whites only long enough to mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 10 x 4-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 300°.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Beat butter and shortening for 30 seconds.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating until well combined.
Cover and chill 3 hours.
Work with 1/2 dough at a time on a lightly floured surface to 1/8th thickness.
Cut into desired shapes. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until done.
Makes 36 to 38.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Saute onions, pepper and chicken in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve over rice. Delicious!

title: hot buttered shrimp
