directions: Combine melted butter, Tabasco sauce and garlic seasoning. Place shrimp in bottom of broiler pan and squeeze lemon juice over them.
Lay onion rings all over shrimp and then pour butter sauce over shrimp and onions.
Broil on one side for a few minutes (not too close to heat) until tender, but not done.
Turn with spatula once and broil other side for short time until nice and pink.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Saute beef in shortening; add garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Cover; cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles according to directions. Drain.
Add onion tops to cream cheese and sour cream; put layer of noodles, cream mixture, meat sauce. Repeat.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake about 25 minutes.

title: chocolate date cake
directions: Boil 1 1/4 cups water; pour over chopped dates.
Let cool. Mix shortening, sugar and eggs; set aside.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Alternate mixing 2nd mixture into 1st with the date mixture.
Place in 13 x 9-inch greased cake pan.
Mix chopped walnuts, chocolate chips and 1/4 cup sugar.
Sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: indian pilau
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt butter or margarine over medium heat. Add onion, ginger, cumin, coriander, cinnamon and red pepper flakes. Cook, stirring 3 minutes.

title: barbecue beef brisket
directions: Pierce meat all over with a large fork, both sides.
Place in large roasting pan.
Sprinkle meat with tenderizing salt and liquid smoke.
Combine onion, salt, pepper, garlic salt and paprika, then sprinkle over meat.
Cover entire top of meat with brown sugar. Cover pan with foil.
Roast in slow oven (325°) for 22 to 25 minutes per pound.
Remove from pan and let stand 1/2 hour.
Before slicing, skim fat from pan juices; combine juices with an equal amount of barbecue sauce.
Heat and serve with meat.

title: jello punch
directions: Bring 4 cups water and sugar to a boil.
Stir until dissolved. Add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cool and freeze.
Remove from freezer 10 hours before serving.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients, spreading over first layer.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter (oleo) until browned.
Mix all together.

title: paella
directions: Steam or boil all seafood.
Cook rice.
Mix all ingredients together and bake 20 minutes.

title: rice broccoli
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Cook broccoli as directed on package except use 1/2 cup of water.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Put in casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Water chestnuts may also be added if desired.
Regular rice may be used if cooked first.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix butter and crumbs and pat into a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 375°.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream together.
Mix together and spread in a 9 x 13 pan (greased).
Sprinkle on part of topping.
Spread on remaining batter, then the rest of topping.
Top with nuts.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; mix until smooth.
Working in batches, dip tomato slices into batter; allow excess to drip back into bowl.
Fry in 2 inches hot oil (375°) in a large, heavy skillet until browned, turning once carefully with tongs. Transfer to a colander to drain.
Do not drain on paper towels, as this will make them soggy.
Stand them up like wheels in the serving dish, instead of stacking them.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Pour half on bottom of greased pan.
Sprinkle with cheese over batter.
Add remaining batter.
Cover with rest of cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Top bread
with 3 slices of dry beef, then add a tablespoon of sauerkraut and a slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Spread Thousand Island dressing and brown in a skillet.

title: ellen brown's broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Pour over broccoli, bacon, cheese and onions.
Stir together.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Melt margarine. Add sugar, milk, cornstarch and salt. Cook until it bubbles. Pour into baked pie shell and sprinkle lightly with cinnamon and nutmeg. Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cover bottom of buttered baking dish with 3 cups of bread crumbs.
Drain off some of the tomato juice.
Mix tomatoes with onion, salt and pepper.
Pour over crumbs in baking dish.
Cover remaining crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until crumbs are brown.

title: peanut butter french toast
directions: Blend peanut butter and applesauce.
Spread mixture on 4 slices white bread.
Top with remaining bread slices.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add salt, sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Dip sandwiches in this egg mixture and fry in butter.

title: beets and pineapple
directions: Heat slowly until juice thickens.

title: quick and easy swedish meatballs
directions: Blend cream of celery soup with water in casserole or saucepan. Measure out 1/4 cup soup mixture and combine in bowl with ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion and parsley.
Shape mixture into balls, about 1-inch in diameter.
Brown on top of stove or microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes.
Add meatballs to remaining soup mixture.
Cook, covered, over low heat about 20 minutes, stirring now and then.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tomato soup
directions: Note:
Instead of a 28 ounce can of tomatoes, I sometimes use 28 ounce can of stewed tomatoes with the cornstarch and tomato paste.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix in a large airtight container.
Use 1/4 to 1/3 cup of mixture to 1 cup hot water.

title: glorified potatoes
directions: Mix
well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hungarian beef
directions: Cut round steak into strips about 2 x 1/2-inches.
Heat heavy frying pan to very hot.
Add meat and stir to begin browning.
Add onion and cook until beef is browned.
Add garlic.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add 1 cup water, catsup, brown sugar, Worcestershire, paprika and mustard.
Simmer until meat is tender, about 30 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and 1/4 cup water, add to meat mixture and stir until sauce has thickened.
Remove from heat and pour over noodles.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine cheese, oil, onion, salt, soup and milk.
Mix rice and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(If you use celery soup, omit the celery.)
tags: cream of celery soup or chicken soup

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O's with 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 1/2 cup cold water with orange juice added.
Grind apples, cranberries, celery and pecans.
Add sugar, pineapple; mix in Jell-O mixture and refrigerate.

title: sproull's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into your favorite bread pan and bake at 450 degrees until done.

title: lemon lush
directions: Blend flour, oleo and nuts and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased).
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool.
Spread blended cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip on cooled crust. Refrigerate.
Beat lemon pudding and milk until thick.
Pour over other layer and refrigerate.
When set, spread remaining Cool Whip over top.

title: crusty potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shortening.
Shape into balls or patties and fry.

title: chocolate chip gingerbread
directions: Follow directions on package.
Pour in pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Gently swirl a little mix to cover chips; do not stir them in.
Bake as directed.
Serve like brownies or as cake with warm applesauce or ice cream.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into cream mixture. Form into walnut-size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press crisscross with fork for shape.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind peeled pears, onions, pepper and all other ingredients. Place in large pot.
Add just enough vinegar to cover (not soupy). Mix well.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Put into hot, sterilized jars. Seal.
Enjoy on peas, beans, etc.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla. Stir in flour.
Add potato chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes, until lightly browned.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: mattie's garlic chicken
directions: Wash and clean chicken.
Place chicken in pan.
Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice, garlic, chopped parsley, seasoned salt and pepper.
Wrap chicken in foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is half way cooked.
Pour sour sauce over the chicken; keep the foil over the chicken.

title: no bake treats
directions: Boil sugar and syrup for 1 minute.
Add butter and peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and corn flakes.
Drop on wax paper.

title: 25 minute cake
directions: Sift together the flour and sugar into a large bowl.
Put oleo, oil, cocoa and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Pour over flour and sugar; mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into a greased and floured pan (11 x 17 x 3/4-inch).
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Mix brown sugar, oleo, salt and sugar flavoring in heavy saucepan; boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in soda.
Pour over popped corn, mixing thoroughly.
Pour onto two cookie sheets with sides. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, stirring often with wooden spoon. Take from oven and separate while still warm.
Let cool. Keep in closed container; stays crisp.
Roasted nuts can be added to popped corn.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Heat soup and melt cheese. Add celery, pecans, onion flakes, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Add gelatin dissolved in water. Pour in 2-quart flat casserole. Arrange spears (cooked and cooled) in lattice fashion on top.
Pretty and good!!!

title: frosting
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Using a mixer, mix the ingredients until smooth and creamy.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a mixing bowl, beat margarine and peanut butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds.
Add 1/2 cup of flour, sugars, egg, baking soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour.
If necessary, cover and chill dough until easy to handle.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
If desired, roll in additional sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten by crisscrossing with tines of a fork.
Bake in a 375° oven for 7 to 9 minutes or until bottoms are lightly browned. Cool cookies on a wire rack.
Makes about 36.

title: evelyn's strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add frozen strawberries and stir until thawed.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 in glass dish and chill.
Spread sour cream on top and spread remaining strawberry mixture over this.
Chill well before serving.
Congeal salad yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Add corn meal last.
If mixture is real dry, add a dash of milk or water.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 350° until brown (30 to 45 minutes).

title: sugar cookies
directions: In mixer, cream sugars and shortening; add eggs one at a time. Combine flour, cream of tartar and soda.
Beat into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Roll into balls and press down on cookie sheet with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° about 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil for 5 minutes the zucchini and onions.
Drain.
Mix stuffing mix with melted butter and water.
Spread 9 x 12-inch pan with stuffing mixture.
Mix drained zucchini with sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: squash pie
directions: Cook sliced unpeeled squash in water until tender; drain. Place all ingredients in blender; blend until seeds disappear. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle with nutmeg after liquid in shell.
(Optional:
Sprinkle with small amount of coconut.)

title: seafoam salad
directions: Heat juice and pour over lime jello while hot.
Add cream cheese that has been mashed with 2 tablespoons cream.
Beat with eggbeater.
Pour in bowl and refrigerate.
Decorate with red cherries.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and ice cubes just before serving.

title: flan
directions: First, you must caramelize the mold.
Put 1 cup of the sugar into the deep mold or pan in which you will bake the custard. Place this over a low flame and stir constantly until the sugar melts and turns a golden color.
Tilt the pan in all directions to evenly coat the bottom and sides.
Set aside to cool while you make the custard.

title: coconut crunch
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Heat oven to 350°.
Put ingredients in cake pan and brown in oven.
Stir occasionally so it does not burn.
Cool.
Mix pudding and milk as directed.
Place 1/2 of the crunch in a layer in a 9-inch square pan.
Spread pudding over, then a layer of Cool Whip.
Top with remaining crunch. Chill.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fruitcake
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat vigorously with spoon or electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Sift 2 cups flour with baking powder, salt and spices.
Stir into the oil mixture alternately with fruit juice.
Mix other cup flour with the fruits and nuts.
Pour batter over the fruit, mixing well.
Turn into 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans, greased and lined with brown paper.
I use a tube pan.
Place pan of water on lower oven rack.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
After baking, let cake stand 15 minutes before removing from pans.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Pour the boiling water over the margarine. Mix in the flour real well. Add eggs, one egg at a time, beating well. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Let cool 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake for 70 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Soften oleo; add eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Blend.
Add dry ingredients; blend well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: ground beef fajitas
directions: Cook meat until nearly done, then add chili powder, fajita seasoning, bell pepper and onion.
Cook until bell peppers are ready.
Serve with flour tortillas, sour cream and any other toppings you prefer.

title: peanut butter fudge candy
directions: Cream oleo and peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan with wax paper so it won't stick to hands.
Melt Hershey bar and pour over top.
Cut into squares. Best to let set overnight so chocolate won't crack.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.
Serve with cauliflower or broccoli.

title: absolutely yummy garden burgers
directions: Mix ingredients well and make 4 patties.
Heat a small amount of oil (I like canola) in nonstick skillet to medium.
Brown patties on both sides, they are a little crispy (for better texture).
Melt cheese on top and serve immediately because they cool off a bit faster than meat burgers.
Use your favorite meat-burger toppings.

title: chicken tetrazzini bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan over medium heat, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, sage and pepper.
Cook until bubbly.
Stir in broth, milk and mushrooms. Cook and stir until mixture boils and is slightly thickened.
Stir in remaining ingredients except Swiss cheese.
Spoon into ungreased 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish.
Sprinkle with Swiss cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.
If desired, sprinkle with chopped fresh parsley. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: french apple pie
directions: Toss the first 3 ingredients gently and put into deep dish pie plate or casserole dish.
Mix together the remaining ingredients. Pour over apples.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 3/4 to 1 stick melted margarine. Put in 13 x 9-inch pan to form crust.
Combine powdered sugar, eggs and 2 sticks margarine and beat for a full 15 minutes with electric mixer.
Then spread on crust.
Next, slice bananas lengthwise and put on sugar mixture layer.
Drain pineapple and spread over bananas.
Spread large container of Cool Whip on top of pineapple.
Top with chopped nuts and halved cherries.
Chill 16 hours before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add cold water, pineapple, bananas and marshmallows (rinse dust from marshmallows first).
Mix well and chill until set.

title: spicy orange salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix thoroughly. Serve over fish fillets.

title: benton balls
directions: Mix well with hands all ingredients, except chocolate chips and wax.
Form into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Put in refrigerator on cookie sheet.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda together. Cream margarine, eggs, sugars and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients. Add oatmeal and coconut.
Bake at 375° until done.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter until forms soft ball in water. Add marshmallows and stir until dissolved.
Add vanilla, graham crackers and nuts.
Drop by spoonful onto buttered cookie sheet.

title: chocolate peanut butter no bake cookies
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients on medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 1 minute; add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Drop on waxed paper by teaspoon.

title: red buttermilk cake
directions: Mix vinegar and soda in a cup; let stand.
Cream sugar and shortening, then add eggs.
Mix well.
Add cocoa and red coloring. Add buttermilk, salt, flour, vanilla, vinegar and soda.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stacie's "no name spaghetti special"
directions: Cut slices of pepperoni in half, fry until edges curl.
Add onions and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Toss with hot cooked spaghetti and combined remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly. Sprinkle with additional parmesan cheese, if desired.
Keep warm.

title: apple crisp
directions: Coat apples with lemon juice to prevent browning.
Mix together flour, brown sugar, oatmeal, cinnamon and butter.
Stir in apples.
Place in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: kraft macaroni and cheese pizza
directions: Prepare dinner as
directed
on package.
Add eggs; mix well. Spread onto greased
12-inch
round
pizza	pan or 13 x 9-inch cookie sheet.
Bake
at
for 10 minutes.
Combine sauce, mushrooms, onions
and green peppers (add whatever else you like over dinner mixture).
Top with pepperoni and cheese. Continue baking 10 minutes.	You can also substitute pepperoni for 1 pound sausage.

title: dutch snap beans
directions: Cook bacon until limp and curling, saving the grease.
In a large pan or Dutch oven, saute onions and garlic in butter over low heat.
Add green beans, tomatoes, tomato juice, bacon, bacon grease and white wine.
Season with salt, pepper and basil.
Cover and let the mixture simmer for 30 minutes or until beans are tender.
Add small amounts of wine or water if the sauce reduces too much during the cooking.
There should be about 1/2 cup liquid remaining when the beans are cooked.
Makes 6 servings.

title: one pot pork chop supper
directions: In skillet, brown chops and pour off fat.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add enough flour to make stiff mix with mixer until it gets too thick.
Then put on counter; put flour on counter and mix for 5 to 10 minutes, kneading good.
Put in a pan sprayed with Pam.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Then work again, dividing dough into 4 pieces.
Make 4 loaves.
Cover dough with clean cloth; let raise again until double.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: mother's date cake
directions: Sprinkle soda over dates.
Pour boiling water over dates and soda.
Put nuts in some of flour.
Mix all good and bake.

title: squash casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend in mayonnaise, onion, green pepper and thyme.
Mix well.
Add to cooked squash.
Butter a casserole. Sprinkle cheese over top and dot with butter.
Put in fridge after it is covered with Saran Wrap.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: herb rice
directions: Bring water to a boil and then add rest of the ingredients. Cover and then cook for 20 minutes on low heat.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Combine and beat together flour, baking powder, salt, pudding, butter, egg and milk.
Pour into a 9 or 10-inch deep dish pie pan. Layer peaches over batter. Combine cream cheese, sugar and peach juice.
Mix for 2 minutes.
Put cream cheese mix to within 1-inch of the edge.
Sprinkle 2 teaspoons cinnamon over the cream cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: toll house kookie brittle
directions: Combine butter, vanilla and salt. Blend; gradually add sugar, flour, chips and nuts. Press into 15 x 10 x 1-inch (jelly roll) pan. Press lightly into pan. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Watch close; will burn easily. Cool. Then break into pieces, but do not cut.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in a greased casserole dish.
Take remaining ingredients and mix until crumbly with a fork and then sprinkle over the apples.
Take 1/2 cup melted butter and pour over mixture.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beer stew
directions: Brown chuck, onions and garlic in oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
To the beef, add beer, bay leaf and thyme; cook until nice and tender.
Serve with whole peeled, boiled potatoes.

title: spaghetti napoli
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute 1 minute.
Add green and red peppers and mushrooms. Saute 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and juice, basil and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes.
Toss with cooked spaghetti and cheese.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pepperidge farm casserole
directions: Melt butter; pour over stuffing.
Place 1/2 of stuffing mixture in a large baking dish.
Bone and cut chicken into medium size pieces.
Combine with peas, milk, soup and onion in a saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over stuffing, then top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Pour 1/2 cup chicken broth over casserole to make if more moist (before baking).

title: party pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese, salad dressing and onions.
Spread on tortillas.
Sprinkle on remaining ingredients, then roll and wrap tightly.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut off roll ends.
Cut rolls into 1-inch slices.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: baked marinated chicken breasts
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Place chicken in shallow baking dish.
Pour sour cream mixture over and marinate, covered in refrigerator overnight, turning occasionally. Dip each piece in crumbs, leaving some marinade on pieces.
Shape into bundles.
Place in ungreaased baking sheet.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours or longer.
Place in 325° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: dilled oyster crackers
directions: In large bowl, place crackers and drizzle salad mix over; toss several times for approximately a day.
Then store in airtight container.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion soup mix and ripe olives well.
Spread a thin layer of this mixture onto a slice of ham.
Top with a slice of cheese and spread a thin layer of mixture on top.
Roll lengthwise.
Wrap tightly in foil and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Continue process with remaining ham, cheese and mixture.
Slice thinly and place on round rye crackers.
Serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix cheese and Bisquick together.
Add sausage.
Roll into marble (bite size) balls.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix spaghetti sauce with cooked macaroni.
Pour into 9 x 11 casserole.
Put on top of mixture in following order:
mozzarella cheese, pepperoni slices, mushrooms, drained.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pizza roll(recipe makes 2 rolls)
directions: *Will take 1 to 2 hours to thaw on cabinet or can be put in refrigerator overnight.

title: banana-bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine cereal and next 5 ingredients.
In another bowl, mix milk, oil, eggs and bananas.
Stir milk mixture into cereal just until combined.
Place in muffin papers and sprinkle almonds on top.
In microwave, cook on High for 4 1/2 to 6 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: nutra-pizza
directions: Put all ingredients in a frying pan.
Add spices: oregano, parsley and basil.
Cook until most water is evaporated.
Take low-fat Mozzarella cheese and put on top.
Cover with lid.
Cook until cheese melts.
Slices like pizza.

title: super corn
directions: Beat.
Add Jiffy corn muffin mix, 1 chopped onion, 1 can cream-style corn and 1 whole kernel corn (drained).
Pour into a 9 x 12 inch buttered baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Pimento may be added for color.

title: one pot stew
directions: Mix. Bake at 325° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until thick.
Put the dry strawberry jello into this mixture and stir well.
Add the strawberries and let set for 5 minutes.
Put in baked pie shell and chill.
Use favorite topping.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Work in shortening until blended.
Add milk and egg, beaten together.
Mix well; add blueberries until just blended; put in muffin pans (greased).
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: hidden valley ranch nachos
directions: Arrange chips in shallow baking dish. Pour salad dressing over chips. Sprinkle cheese and green onions evenly over chips and dressing. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until cheese is melted slightly.

title: bread pudding #1
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, milk, salt, vanilla and crumbled biscuits.
Grease loaf pan with oleo or butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti pizza deluxe
directions: Prepare spaghetti per package directions.
In medium bowl, blend milk and egg.
Add spaghetti; toss to coat.
Spray a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Spread spaghetti mixture evenly in pan.
In large skillet, cook beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until beef is no longer pink; drain.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings; simmer for 5 minutes. Spoon meat mixture evenly over spaghetti.
Top with mushrooms and cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Makes 8 servings,
Each serving contains 267 calories, 9.2 g fat, 498.8 mg sodium and 76.4 mg cholesterol.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Then add the next 3 ingredients.
Mix well and add all the other ingredients.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup chocolate chips and 1/2 to 3/4 cup chopped nuts on top. Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in casserole.
Add other ingredients. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes. Serves 3 to 4.

title: oriental seafood salad
directions: Combine
first	5 ingredients, then mix mayonnaise, soy sauce, lemon
juice
and	ginger	together.
Add to the first mixture, then
just before serving toss in 1 can of chow mein noodles.

title: orange-pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake in 3 layers after mixing all ingredients together. Bake as directed on box.
Cool completely.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Mix first six ingredients and pour in pan.
Mix last three ingredients and pour over this.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix with cream cheese and 1/2 stick margarine.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Put mixed ingredients into a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Thaw as directed.
Cut lengthwise in half.
Cut each half into 7 equal parts.
With greased hands, roll each piece into a ball and place in a greased pan.
Allow to raise.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: politician's cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions and let cool. Poke holes in cake with a fork. Pour pineapple on cake. Mix pudding and pour over cake. Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Add oil and applesauce. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine rhubarb, 1/2 cup sugar and flour.
Spoon into pie shell.

title: let's wok
directions: Heat oil.
Brown beef
about
2 minutes.
Pull to sides of wok.
Add other ingredients and cook 15 minutes.
Place top on wok and steam 5 to
7 minutes.	Cooking time will depend on how crunchy you like the vegetables.
This
is	good
as is or may be served on a bed of rice.

title: sour cream irish bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Add sour cream. Mix well.
Add well beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add raisins.
Grease and flour pan.
After batter is in pan, pour melted butter evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test center.
May take 1 1/2 hours.

title: teriyaki tofu hamburger
directions: Drain tofu for 15 minutes in colander.
Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup of teriyaki sauce (reserve 1/2 cup for later). Form into approximately 16 to 18 patties.
Brown in skillet sprayed with Pam.
Add remaining 1/2 cup teriyaki sauce and continue cooking for few minutes until sauce is thickened and forms glaze.

title: chipped beef spread
directions: Mix together well. Good on crackers or bread.

title: ice cream candy
directions: Melt margarine.
Gradually add powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and enough canned milk to make dough that can be rolled out.
Roll out on floured board and cover with peanut butter.
Roll up as a jelly roll.
Chill.
Slice into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: chicken goulash
directions: *You might want to start with less paprika, especially if it is the hot variety.

title: fruited cake
directions: Mix into bowl.
Put half the batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1 cup pie filling, then add remaining batter and sprinkle with crushed walnuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pan and serve.

title: orange chicken chunks
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt and paprika.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add chicken and cook 5 minutes until white.
Add syrup from pineapple, chicken broth and vinegar.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add celery, green pepper and onion.
Cover; cook 5 minutes.
Add tomato wedges and pineapple chunks.
Blend soy sauce, brown sugar, cornstarch and water.
Add to sauce; stir constantly until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Add orange sections and toss lightly.
Serve over fried rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Defrost broccoli; drain, but do not cook.
Mix broccoli, Bisquick, milk, cheese and egg.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until brown on top.

title: cool summer cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions.
Remove and allow to cool. Poke holes in cake with fork.
Mix Jell-O using 1 cup only of water.
Pour Jell-O over cake, making sure all holes have Jell-O in them.
Refrigerate until Jell-O is set in cake.
Cover with Cool Whip when ready to serve.
Cut into squares and garnish with strawberries, if desired.

title: shoe string potato salad
directions: The above ingredients may be fixed ahead of time and chilled in the refrigerator.
Just before serving, add 1 (4 ounce) bag or can of shoestring potatoes.
Serve on lettuce cups.

title: anadama bread
directions: Heat water, cornmeal, salt, butter or margarine and molasses in medium size saucepan until thick and bubbly.
Pour into a large bowl; cool to lukewarm, about 45 minutes.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add water, egg and soup; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello and flour together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake according to box directions.

title: beef 'n cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large skillet, brown ground meat and season with salt and pepper. Drain. In a bowl, whisk together tomato soup, tomato sauce and water and stir until smooth.

title: banana walnut gift loaf
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs; beat until light.
Add bananas and stir in sifted flour.
Add walnuts. Bake in a loaf pan.

title: broccoli hot dish
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in a large baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fudge pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, cocoa and vanilla.
Mix at low speed until blended.
Beat whole eggs and egg yolks.
Add cocoa mixture.
Slowly stir in Pet milk. Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
The filling should be firm.
The time will vary according to your stove.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Scald pineapple.
Mix cornstarch, salt, sugar and stir into pineapple.
Stir and cook slowly 10 minutes.
Add lemon juice and beaten egg yolks slowly.
Cover and let cook 5 minutes.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with whipped cream when ready to serve. Good when chilled.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Blend first four ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix eggs and beat for 3 minutes.
Add drained oranges.
Bake in a greased and floured pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cool in pan.

title: tropical dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the cherry pie filling on bottom; spread undrained pineapple in second layer, then dump cake mix on top.
Do not mix the ingredients.
Pour butter evenly over batter, then spread coconut.
Finally, sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 325° until golden.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown sausage with onion and green pepper.
Cook pasta shells according to directions and drain.
Drain sausage and combine with pasta.
Add sauce and garlic or Italian seasoning to taste. Spoon into lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Layer 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, pepperoni, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: sure thing brownies
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Blend for 2 minutes. Add nuts. Beat for 1 more minute. Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal-raisin bread
directions: Combine whole-wheat flour, brown sugar, salt, butter (softened), oats, raisins and boiling water and stir. Cool mixture to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water. Stir to melt butter. Gradually stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.

title: tony's dirty rice
directions: Mix together and put into casserole dish and bake in 350° oven until rice is done.

title: calico bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Mix together lightly and cover with dressing. Refrigerate for several hours.
When ready to serve, mix again. Taste and add more vinegar or seasoning, if needed.
Serve in a large bowl and garnish with tomato wedges and onion rings.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 stick margarine, 1 egg, water and nuts.
Press into bottom of greased oblong pan.
It will look like cookie dough.
In a bowl, soften the cream cheese.
Add 1 stick melted butter, 2 eggs and 1 box powdered sugar; whip with mixer.
Pour over first layer.
Cook until top is brown, about 30 minutes, at 350°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar, cooked rice and lemon extract; mix well.
Cook over low heat.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Add butter after removing from heat.
Place in baking dish.
Beat egg whites until foamy; spread on pudding.
Broil for about 1 minute or until top is brown.

title: petite cherry cheese cakes
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy. Line small muffin pans with 24 paper cups. Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of peach. Fill cups 2/3 full with cheese mixture. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or just until set. Top each with about 1 tablespoon cherry pie filling. Chill. Makes about 2 dozen cakes.

title: mayonnaise cake(a recipe from the whidbey pioneer sill family.)
directions: Cream the shortening and honey; add egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with sour milk.

title: tuna on a shoestring
directions: In large bowl, separate tuna into chunks. Add carrots, celery, onion and salad dressing; toss until tuna is well coated with dressing. Cover and chill. Just before serving, fold in potatoes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: heath candy bar
directions: Line a cookie sheet with heavy foil.
Place crackers on sheets (7 rows x 5 rows).
Boil margarine, butter and sugar exactly 3 minutes.
Drizzle mixture over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with chocolate chips.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Coat at 10-inch Bundt pan with cooking spray.
Dust with flour.
Beat sugar and oil at medium speed with electric mixer 1 minute.
Add egg substitute, 1/4 cup at a time, beating after each addition.

title: bread pudding
directions: Layer bread in buttered shallow baking dish.
Scald milk with oleo.
Beat egg slightly and sugar; stir in vanilla and nutmeg. Pour milk mixture over bread.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake in glass dish in pan of boiling water until center is set and bread brown, about 40 minutes at 325°.
Serve hot with ice cream.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Saute onion.
Flour chicken and fry until brown.
Place chicken and onion in casserole.
Bring to a boil celery, green pepper, catsup, water, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Leftover sauce can be saved and used in other recipes.

title: brown sugar franks
directions: Take beef wieners and bacon, wrap each piece of wiener in bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle brown sugar over wieners, then sprinkle a little cinnamon over that.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drain off grease.

title: hot zucchini-carrot slaw
directions: Shred zucchini and carrots.
Heat oil with garlic in a large skillet.
Add vegetables, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring, until crisp-tender (3 to 5 minutes).

title: pear mincemeat
directions: Put pears, apples, oranges, lemons, raisins, grape juice, sugar and vinegar in large pot. Bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes.
Add cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Simmer another 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Blend sugar and cream cheese together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Place in cupcake containers.
Freeze.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, covered.
Uncover last 5 minutes.

title: quick fudge frosting
directions: Mix granulated sugar and cocoa in saucepan.
Stir in margarine, milk, corn syrup and salt.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently.
Boil, stirring occasionally, 3 minutes.
Cool.
Beat in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Frosts an 8-inch 2 layer cake.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Heat on High power for 3 minutes in microwave the chocolate chips and Eagle Brand condensed milk.
Add vanilla.
Stir well. May add marshmallows or nuts.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch foiled-lined pan.
Let cool.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese into shallow dish ( like a pie plate).
Sprinkle chopped olives onto cheese.
Pour sauce onto olives.
Sprinkle cheese onto sauce.
Then sprinkle green onions on top of cheese.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Grease 12 x 8-inch Pyrex pan.
Mix pudding with milk.
Blend pudding and Cool Whip.
Line Pyrex with graham crackers.
Spread 1/3 pudding mix on crackers.
Add second layer of crackers.
Top with 1/3 pudding mix.
Third layer of crackers.
Top with final 1/3 pudding mix.
Fourth layer of crackers.
Freeze one hour and frost with chocolate frosting.
Freeze at least 2 days.
Cover.
Thaw to serve.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 9 minutes (do not overbake, cookies will be soft; they will puff while baking and flatten while cooling).
Cool slightly. Remove from cookie sheet onto wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: mashed potato cake
directions: Cream the oil and sugar. Add other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: willamsburg french dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a jar.
Add vinegar; cover and allow to steep a few minutes.
Makes 1 cup.

title: stuffed mushrooms italian
directions: Cut ends from mushrooms. Remove stems from mushrooms. Chop stems finely.
Cook and stir mushroom stems, green onions and garlic in butter over medium heat until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Fill mushroom caps with stuffing mixture.
Place mushrooms, filled side up, in a greased baking dish.
Cook in a 350° oven for 15 minutes. Serve hot.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish. Place sliced cheese on each piece. Stir together soup and wine (if desired). Spoon over chicken. Sprinkle on stuffing mix and drizzle with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot taco rice
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet. Add salsa, tomato sauce and bouillon cube.
Bring to full boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve beef mixture over rice.
Top with tomatoes, sour cream, cheese or chips.

title: lime fizz
directions: Just before serving, combine the limeade concentrate, syrup and quinine water in a pitcher.
Add food coloring to tint desired shade of green; mix lightly.
Garnish with a float of fresh cranberries.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks and add all the other ingredients except whites.
Put in a double boiler and let it cook until it's real thick.
Put in cooked pie shell.
Put the meringue on it and let it brown.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream sugar, butter or margarine and peanut butter. Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt. Stir into egg mixture. Shape into balls (teaspoon each). Roll in additional granulated sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Immediately press chocolate candy kiss into each cookie.

title: meatless mushroom burgers
directions: Heat the broiler (these are difficult to cook on an outdoor grill).
In a medium frying pan, heat oil over high heat.
Add mushrooms, zucchini and onion; cook until the vegetables are softened and the liquid evaporates, 5 to 6 minutes.
Add garlic and 1 tablespoon of the steak sauce and cook until the steak sauce begins to evaporate, 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in the parsley, basil and oregano, remove pan from heat and allow mixture to cool.
In a large bowl, beat together the Ricotta cheese and egg until smooth. Add cooled vegetable mixture, wheat germ, oats and remaining steak sauce.
Mix to blend well.
Divide mixture in fourths, shaping each portion into a 1 1/4-inch thick patty.
Place patties on a foil-lined cookie sheet.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill until firm, at least 1 hour.
Set patties on broiler pan or a foil-lined cookie sheet and cook, turning once, until done, 6 to 7 minutes per side.
The outside should be well browned and burgers should feel firm to the touch.
Split rolls and toast.
Serve burgers in toasted rolls with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: ms culver's strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve jello in water, add flour, oil and unbeaten eggs to cake mix, beat with mixer at medium speed until smooth; add strawberries, beat 1 minute.
Pour in 9 x 13 greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350 F for 30-35 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat
oven
Saute onions and green pepper in fat until
onions turn yellow.	Add meat and fry until mixture falls apart.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking
dish;
cover and bake for 1 hour.
Remove lid the last 15 minutes.

title: fruit pound cake
directions: Mix all together. Pour into Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: cherry bounce
directions: Wash and stem cherries. Place all in a large jar or bottle. Cover tightly and up-end jar daily until all sugar is dissolved. Place in cool dark place for at least 2 months. Serve in liqueur glasses. Yield: 1 quart.

title: fudge candy
directions: Combine milk and cocoa in a saucepan.
Cook and beat over low heat until cocoa is dissolved.
Add butter, fructose, salt and vanilla.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook for 2 minutes. Remove from heat; add cereal crumbs and work in with wooden spoon. Cool 15 minutes.
Divide dough in half; roll each half into an 8-inch long tube.
Roll each tube in the finely chopped nuts. Wrap in waxed paper and chill overnight.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix pumpkin, eggs and oil.
Mix dry ingredients and stir in alternately with water.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: light cocoa frosting
directions: In a small mixing bowl stir together whipped topping, milk, cocoa and vanilla.
Beat on high speed of mixer about 4 minutes or until soft peaks form.
Spread on cake.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix oat bran cereal, brown sugar and baking powder in large bowl.
Mix skim milk, first can of pineapple, eggs and oil in bowl or blender.
Then add to dry ingredients.
Drain second can of pineapple and add to mixture. Line muffin pan with paper baking cups and fill with batter.
Bake 17 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: favorite jam cake
directions: Cream the butter with sugar.
Add egg yolks and mix well. Sift flour with spices.
Add dry ingredients.

title: grilled flank steak(low cholesterol)
directions: For sauce:
In small saucepan, cook onion, garlic and chili powder in margarine until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, vinegar, honey, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened.

title: surprise seafood gumbo
directions: Put shrimp in a big old pot, then put oysters in.
I think biscuits go in the pot next.
Then you put in a fish.
Cut and peel one apple and orange and put in pot.
Stir.
Add 1 bag of corn and taters.
Cook 1 or 2 hours, then eat it.

title: quick and easy
directions: Brown sausage
and drain.
Saute celery in butter until soft. Mix all together in a Dutch oven and heat.

title: mom's orange pie
directions: Cook all ingredients until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell and put oleomargarine on top and brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Roll, then cut cookies.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: beef noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles 10 minutes.
Brown beef in hot shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat slowly until bouillon cube is dissolved.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 10 servings.

title: beef dip
directions: Mix cheese, sour cream, milk and beef.
Add seasonings and mix.
Put in baking dish. Saute pecans in small amount of butter. Sprinkle on top of dip.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: garlic mushrooms in sherry sauce-spain
directions: When oil is hot, throw in minced garlic.
When it's starting to get brownish, add sliced mushrooms.
Cook mushrooms at medium heat until almost done.
Then add crushed hot red peppers, salt and sherry wine according to taste.
Let it boil on high heat for 5 to 7 more minutes.

title: tomato-cheese pizza
directions: Soften yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Set aside.
Pour remaining cup of warm water into a large bowl.
Blend in 2 cups flour and 1 teaspoon salt.
Stir softened yeast and add to flour-water mixture, mixing well.
Add about 1 cup flour to yeast mixture and beat until very smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: indonesian grilled lamb chops
directions: Marinate for 24 hours.
Grill over charcoal.
Serve on a saute of mixed kula greens.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
In bowl, combine potatoes, cheese, onion, parsley and bread crumbs; mix well.
Turn into casserole.
Blend salt, pepper, butter or margarine and milk.
Pour over potato mixture.
Sprinkle with cornflakes.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and Crisco.
Use pastry cutter to mix until crumbly.
Add water.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: one dish pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan with onion (chopped or diced). Drain fat. Remove pork chops.
Add remaining ingredients to frying pan.
Place pork chops back in pan on top of rice.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: mac corn
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: spiced tea
directions: Place 2 heaping teaspoons into mug of hot water.
Enjoy!

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Add taco seasoning mix. Spread in a shallow dish. Top with shredded lettuce, shredded cheese, tomatoes and olives.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: peanut butter dreams
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, soda and salt and set aside.
In large bowl, combine peanut butter, sugar and shortening.
Beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture and blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips and optional raisins.
Shape into walnut-sized balls and press down gently on cookie sheet, retaining round shape.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: bohemian coffee cake
directions: Mix all together and pour in a floured and greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: coconut fried shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp, leaving tails intact; devein.
Combine pancake mix and beer in a small bowl; stir until smooth.
Pour oil to depth of 2 inches into a Dutch oven; heat to 350°.
Dredge shrimp in flour; shake off excess.
Dip shrimp into batter; dredge in coconut.
Fry, a few at a time, 45 seconds on each side or until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Yield:
4 appetizer servings.

title: steamed brown bread
directions: Pour the Mazola, Karo and milk into a mixing bowl.
Add the soda dissolved in one tablespoon of boiling water.
Beat in the cornmeal, salt and raisins.
Transfer to three 1-pound baking powder cans or 1 large mold oiled with Mazola.
Steam for an hour and a half for the small molds or 4 hours for the large one. Serve with butter or with heated Karo (orange label).

title: r.i. clam chowder
directions: Fry salt pork until crisp.
Saute onions.
Add to boiling water along with potatoes and tomato soup.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours. Turn off stove; add quahogs and juice.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add oil slowly and mix well.
Sift flours and soda together; add to egg mixture a little at a time and mix well.
Add apples, nuts and coconut.
Pour into a greased long pan and bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until tested done.

title: crescent dogs 'n cheese
directions: Slit wieners and stuff with cheese.
Roll in crescent rolls. Bake for 25 minutes at 300°.
Serve with mustard or ketchup. Great lunchtime snack.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Cut off excess fat from pork chops.
Let fat melt in skillet until you have about 1 tablespoon melted.
Remove unmelted pieces of fat.
Brown pork chops on each side in melted fat.
Pour off excess fat.
Mix together rest of ingredients and pour over pork chops.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer until done, about 1 hour. Serve hot.
Liquid may be thickened with cornstarch and served with pork chops.
Serves 4.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Saute onion, then add all ingredients, including rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a buttered casserole dish (2 1/2 or 3-quart) for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: creole green beans
directions: Fry bacon; retain grease.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in grease.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Place crumbled bacon on top in serving bowl.

title: baby food bars
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, cinnamon, baby food, baking soda and flour together.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chili relleno casserole
directions: Cut chilies into strips and place in bottom of casserole dish. Cover with cheese. Mix rest of ingredients in bowl and pour over cheese. Top with tomatoes and olives. Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops; set aside.
In casserole dish, mix onion soup mix, rice and mushroom soup.
Add dissolved bouillon cube; mix together.
Lay pork chops on top.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mam maw's fruit cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix the graham crackers, pecans, coconut and raisins.
On very low heat, mix the marshmallows in sweetened condensed milk.
Mix thoroughly with dry ingredients.
Press into foil lined dish.
Stores in refrigerator for weeks.

title: baked potato toppings
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and blend until smooth.
Place desired amount on top of baked potato and sprinkle with paprika.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Cool, but do not chill.
Add sherbet, softened, to jello mixture.
Drain the mandarin oranges; add to jello sherbet mixture.
Stir well.
Pour into 13 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Chill well for several hours or until firm.
Cut in serving pieces.

title: chewy peanut butter and apple cookies
directions: Beat peanut butter and margarine with an electric mixer until soft.
Add brown sugar, half the flour, egg whites, milk and baking soda.
Beat until well combined; stir in remaining flour, rolled oats and apple.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Stir in sherbet and remaining ingredients.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan and congeal.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil; add berries.
When they come to a rolling boil, cook 15 minutes.
Do not stir, but shake pan while berries are cooking.
Pour into shallow pan and let stand 24 hours. It is best to shake pan occasionally while berries are cooling. This will let the juice seep into the berries and make them real plump.
Medium size whole berries are best.
Yields 4 pints.

title: peggy's nappa salad
directions: Chop cabbage and onions.
Bag and refrigerate.
Saute, brown and cool oleo, noodles, sesame seed and almonds.
Boil sugar, vinegar, oil and soy sauce for 1 minute and cool.
Mix together when ready to serve.

title: moist oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil together the first 6 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Add a pinch of salt and set aside to cool.
When cool, add eggs, vanilla, flour, soda and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and chill.

title: chocolate bundt cake
directions: In a mixing bowl combine cake and pudding mixes, sour cream, eggs, oil and water.
Beat on low speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in grated chocolate, chocolate chips and chopped pecans.
Transfer to a greased and floured 10 inch fluted tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Drizzle with frosting and garnish with pecan halves.

title: christmas cake(julekake)
directions: Thoroughly mix the dry yeast with 1/3 of the flour and all the other ingredients.
Heat milk with margarine over low heat until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add liquids to dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed on electric mixer.
Add 1/2 cup of flour. Add eggs and beat on high speed 2 minutes.
Add fruit and stir in additional flour.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Shape into 3 round loaves; let rise and then bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place stick of butter in a loaf style casserole dish and place in oven to melt.
In a large bowl, mix sugar, flour, milk, egg and vanilla.
Fold in fruit.
Remove casserole dish from oven.
Pour batter into dish, do not stir. Bake for 30 minutes.
Good served with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: barb's potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water and salt.
Bring potatoes to boil, then cook on medium heat.
Cook potatoes and chopped onion until potatoes are tender.
Add 2 cups milk and cubed or grated cheese. Do not boil.
When cheese is melted, add rest of milk.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble on pot of soup.
Stir.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Using microwave-proof pan, pour corn syrup and sugar in and stir slightly.
Microwave for 4 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup nuts and microwave for 3 to 5 more minutes.
Stir in salt, butter and vanilla.
Microwave for 1 to 2 more minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir in baking soda.
Pour immediately onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Let set until cool and firm, then break into pieces.

title: yokan
directions: Wash kanten
and
strip.
Add
water; boil until kanten dissolves.	 Add
sugar;	boil
again.	Add
koshian	or tsubushian.
Cook on
low or medium heat for 20 to 30 minutes. Pour into pan and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, cracker crumbs and peanut butter in a medium sized bowl until blended.
Scrape into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish and press into an even layer.
Spread melted chocolate over top.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours, until chocolate is firm. Let stand at room temperature, about 15 minutes, before cutting into bars.

title: condensed milk
directions: Mix in blender.
Refrigerate overnight.
Use in recipes calling for condensed milk.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange lettuce in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In layers, add other vegetables.
Do not toss.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over layer of peas.
Sprinkle with bacon over salad before serving. Cut into squares.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Combine broth, onion, celery, carrots, parsley, pepper, thyme and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil; stir once or twice.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add chicken; simmer, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes or until chicken is cooked.
Remove and discard bay leaf.
Stir in rice and lime juice just before serving.
Garnish with lime slices.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pancakes
directions: Put pancake mix and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pan.
Beat first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining dry ingredients all at once.
Mix by hand just until blended.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.
Makes 1 large loaf or 4 individual loaves.

title: taco tossed salad
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add can of taco sauce.
In bowl, toss the following:
lettuce, bell pepper, tomato, celery, olives and grated cheese.
Add Thousand Island dressing.
Spoon hot meat mixture over all; toss.
Serve with corn chips.
Main dish that serves 6.

title: charlie pride sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: blackberry pudding
directions: Cook and sweeten 1 pint blackberries; set aside.
Cook until thick milk, eggs, flour and sugar.
Add salt and vanilla wafers. Layer of berries, layer of cooked mixture.
Cover with meringue.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble cooled baked cake.
Layer half of the cake crumbs in a clear punch bowl. Top with 1/2 of the pie filling, 1/2 pudding, 1/2 pineapple, 1/2 bananas and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat layers, using remaining 1/2 of each ingredient.
Garnish with pecans, coconut and cherries. Serves 20.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat 1 minute.
Add pineapple and fold in bread.
Bake in buttered 2-cup casserole for 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.
Great accompaniment with ham.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Mix cocoa, sugar, salt and flour.
Add to scalded milk.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat. Add the butter and vanilla to the pudding.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Stir in boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and allow to proof (5 minutes). Add water, yeast mix and beaten eggs to shortening mix.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add beaten eggs. Sift in dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Heat oven to 375°.

title: rum punch
directions: Mix all in punch bowl, top with ice ring.

title: fettuccini alfredo
directions: Prepare noodles as directed.
While noodles are cooking, in a medium saucepan, place butter and cream over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mix bubbles for 2 minutes.
Gradually stir in Parmesan cheese until blended and fairly smooth; do not put back on heat as the sauce will get lumpy and cheese will get tough. Serve over noodles and garnish with parsley.

title: beef and bean enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare hamburger and taco seasoning as directed.
Stir in beans.
Simmer over medium heat until hot, stirring occasionally.
Heat tortillas until warm and flexible. Spoon 1/3 cup hot filling down center of each warm tortilla.
Roll up and place seam down in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour enchilada sauce evenly over them.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 7 x 11-inch pan.
Melt margarine in saucepan with brown sugar; stir together.
Let it come to a boil, then let it bubble for 2 to 3 minutes (on low to medium heat).
Remove from stove and let it cool about 10 minutes. Add eggs and stir well.
Then add vanilla and stir, then add flour and baking powder and stir.
If using nuts, add now.
Scrape into baking dish; add butterscotch bits (about 1/2 cup) to top of batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: grandmother's oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats in boiling water with butter and let set while preparing the other ingredients.
Add oats and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp toast
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Open each English muffin and spread mixture on each half.
Place each piece on cookie pan.
Broil until golden and bubbly.
Cut each English muffin into quarters.
Each muffin makes 8 pieces.
Serve warm.

title: date cookies
directions: Combine sugars and cream into margarine.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add dates, raisins, nuts, chocolate chips of choice.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 15 dozen.

title: tri-level brownies
directions: For bottom layer:
Sift together the 1/2 cup flour, the soda and the first 1/4 teaspoon salt; mix with rolled oats and the brown sugar.
Stir in 6 tablespoons melted butter or margarine. Pat mixture in 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan; bake in moderate oven (350°) for 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing, butter and mayonnaise.
Add chicken and soup. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: simple white cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour 9x9 cake pan or line a muffin pan with paper liners. In a medium bowl, cream together the sugar and butter. Beat in the eggs, one at a time, then stir in the vanilla. Combine flour and baking powder, add to the creamed mixture and mix well. Finally, stir in the milk until batter is smooth. Pour or spoon batter into the pan. Bake for 30-40 minutes. For cupcakes, bake 20-25 minutes. Cake is done when it springs back to the touch.

title: cottage cheese patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into patties.
Fry in oil.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with tomato sauce if desired. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: orange delight
directions: Prepare jello according to the directions on the box.
Prepare Dream Whip according to the directions on its box.
Fold Dream Whip into partly set jello.
Add all remaining ingredients and chill until firm.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a pan with Pam. Spread potatoes in bottom of pan. Melt the butter, stir in the soup and onion. Cook until bubbling. Remove from heat and stir in cheese, reserving some for topping. Pour over potatoes and sprinkle cheese over top. Bake uncovered for 45 minutes to 1 hour. The potatoes should be tender.

title: sally hinds' spaghetti dinner
directions: Combine ground beef, bell pepper and onion.
Cook over medium heat until browned, covered.
Add tomato sauce, water, tomato paste, water, salt, brown sugar, mushrooms and spice mix from dinner box.
Break spaghetti from dinner box into 2-inch pieces and cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain and add to meat mixture. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix lightly.
Cover and chill for at least 2 hours.
Can be eaten hot or cold.

title: irene's super sandwich
directions: You will also need a 2 x 4-inch board covered with foil, 4 to 6-feet long.

title: fruit soup(serve chilled)
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or food processor.
Thicken with more bananas or yogurt.
Or thin with more fruit juice. Float fresh mint on top or violets.
Use on picnics or summer lunches.
Goes great with quiche and a tossed salad.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Melt margarine in 6-quart Dutch oven over medium heat. Cover and cook garlic, celery, carrot and onion in margarine 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in broth and water. Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Stir in tortellini. Cover and simmer about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until tortellini are tender. Stir in parsley, pepper and nutmeg. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Sprinkle each serving with Parmesan cheese.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Heat soups, Milnot, enchilada sauce and chili powder to boiling.
In large dish, layer 1/2 bag chips; spread meat mixture over chips.
Sprinkle 3/4 cheese.
Pour sauce over all.
Top with more Doritos and rest of cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable relish salad
directions: Drain the first 3 ingredients.
Add the next 5 ingredients.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add egg and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins and nuts, if desired.
Spoon into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroni or spaghetti and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni (spaghetti) until tender and drain.

title: taco bake
directions: Cut tortillas into 1-inch pieces and set aside.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs, milk, bread crumbs, onion, salt, chili powder and peppers.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Put mixture into 8 1/4 x 1 1/4-inch round baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Drain off excess fat.
Combine catsup, brown sugar and mustard; spread over meat loaf.
Rrturn to oven for 10 minutes more.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: pan fried chicken(amish recipe)
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Cut up chicken; roll in flour mixture and brown in butter until browned on both sides.
Place in a baking dish and cover "bottom of dish" with water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until tender.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all together and place in a pie plate.
Cover with shredded Monterey Jack cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: roasted autumn vegetables
directions: In large bowl, toss potatoes, shallots, 4 tablespoons oil, bay leaf, dried thyme, garlic salt and pepper.
Spread in oiled large roasting pan.
Roast at 375°.
Shake pan every 5 to 10 minutes for 25 minutes.
In bowl, toss squash with remaining 1 tablespoon oil, salt and pepper; add to pan.
Roast vegetables; shake pan for 10 to 20 minutes, until tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Season as desired.
Serves 8.

title: cookies and cream pie
directions: Line bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate with cookies.
Blend milk and ice cream in medium bowl.
Add pie filling mix.
Beat with wire whisk or at low speed of electric mixer until blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour immediately into pie plate.
Chill until set, about 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping if desired.
Makes 8 servings.
Preparation Time:
15 minutes.

title: norwegian cabbage slaw
directions: Heat liquids, sugar and salt to near boiling and pour over cabbage mixture.
Do not stir until cool.
Will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to egg and sugar mixture.
Add nuts and blend well.
This makes 2 cakes.
I use two 9 x 13-inch glass dishes or a Bundt pan and a small tube pan.

title: stir-fried chicken and veggies
directions: In cup, blend soy sauce, cornstarch and 1 cup water until smooth; set aside.
In Dutch oven or wok, stir-fry chicken and pepper strips in very hot oil until lightly browned.
Stir in soy sauce mixture and cook until sauce boils.
Add broccoli and bamboo shoots, stirring to break up broccoli.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 8 minutes or just until broccoli is tender-crisp.
Serve with rice. Serves 4.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and level.
Place in refrigerator overnight and mix again in the morning.
Let set 2 days.
Mix burger and place between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Roll the burger out to desired thickness.
Put in freezer until it hardens, then remove and cut in strips.
Place in dehydrator overnight or until done.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Quarter tomatoes and grate the cheese.
Fry meat, onion, pepper and garlic; drain.
Add beans, seasoning and tomatoes. Line 9-inch baking dish with 6 tortillas, slightly overlapped. Top with 1/2 meat mix.
Add 1/3 of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining tortillas, sauce and cheese.

title: southern peach fluff
directions: Beat jello, pineapple with juice and sugar until jello and sugar has melted. Let cool. Then fold in whipped topping, buttermilk and chopped nuts. Refrigerate until firm.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine and vanilla in heavy pot. Boil 9 minutes on medium-high heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add peanut butter. Mix well, then add marshmallow cream. Mix well and pour in 9 x 13 buttered dish. Cool and cut in squares.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in milk and coat with bread crumbs.
Lightly fry in olive oil for 3 minutes.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Pour some of the sauce over and sprinkle additional grated Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° and serve with angel hair pasta.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in blueberries.
Add milk, eggs and butter.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Do not overbeat.
Spoon batter into 12 greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: coconut surprise sheet cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix as directed on package.
Add coconut and coconut flavoring (this makes the cake light).
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the canned milk, powdered sugar, vanilla and coconut flavoring while the cake is baking.
Use a 2-cup measure and add enough water at the end to make a total of 1 3/4 cups liquid.
As soon as cake is removed, punch holes all over the top with a fork.
Pour the liquid over the warm cake.
Use all the liquid.
When the cake is cool, top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate.
If desired, when serving, top each piece with a cherry.

title: pineapple raisin drops
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add vanilla, beaten egg, raisins and pineapple.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Makes 40 cookies.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: In double
boiler,
melt mustard and jelly; add wieners and boil 5 minutes. Serve warm.
Makes about 50.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease baking pan generously with butter and put rice in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle half of onion soup mix on rice.
Place 8 pieces of chicken on rice and sprinkle other half of onion soup mix over chicken.
Add can of mushroom soup (spoon it on the chicken pieces).
Add 1 can of water.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika. Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carylion's banana bread
directions: Mix approximately 1 minute.
Divide into 2 greased and floured loaf pans or can make into cupcakes.
Makes approximately 18 large ones.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes for a loaf or approximately 20 to 25 minutes for cupcakes.

title: apple spice syrup
directions: In saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch, allspice and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Add juice or cider.
Cook and stir over medium heat until syrup is bubbly and slightly thickened.
Yield:
1 3/4 cups.

title: corn and chicken dinner
directions: In a Dutch oven, melt butter.
Add chicken and garlic.
Cook over high heat, stirring occasionally until chicken is golden brown (10 to 15 minutes).
Break corn into 3 pieces each.
Reduce heat to medium and add remaining ingredients except zucchini and tomatoes.
Cover and cook until chicken is fork-tender (20 to 25 minutes).
Cut zucchini into 2-inch pieces.
Cut tomato into 1-inch pieces.
Place zucchini on top of chicken and corn mixture. Cover and steam 3 to 6 minutes.
Add tomatoes; cover and let stand 5 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas(nice and filling)
directions: Cut chicken into strips and salt.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, saute onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chilies, sugar, cumin, salt, oregano and basil. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, 20 minutes. Remove from heat.
Dip each tortilla into tomato mixture to soften. Place two pieces of chicken and 2 kinds of cheeses on each tortilla.
Roll up and place seam down in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend sour cream into remaining sauce mixture and pour over enchiladas.
Sprinkle top with any remaining cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, then crushed bananas and nuts.
Bake in moderate oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top of bread as it goes in the oven for extra goodness.

title: zucchini hot dish
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in salt water until done; drain. Brown hamburger and drain.
Prepare stuffing mix, following directions on box.
Mix meat and zucchini with carrots, soup and sour cream.

title: mexican beef hash
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients until meat is browned; drain, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bake in covered casserole dish at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bow ties
directions: Beat eggs; add cream, butter, salt and vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder.
Knead.
Roll out part of dough thin.
Cut into strips.
Form ties.
Fry quickly.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: "frosty"
directions: Mix all ingredients together in ice cream freezer.
Freeze as usual.
Tastes like a "frosty."

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a large microwavable bowl, mix peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Cook in microwave on High 6 to 7 minutes.
Mixture should be bubbly and peanuts lightly browned.
Quickly stir in butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes more.
Add baking soda and stir quickly until mixture is foamy.
Immediately pour onto a greased baking sheet.
Let cool for 15 minutes or longer.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container.
Makes 14 to 16 servings.

title: meatballs with lemon sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Shape into 12 (1 1/2-inch) balls.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water; reduce heat. Add meatballs to bouillon.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove meatballs and keep warm.
Add lemon juice to bouillon.
Dissolve cornstarch in cold water.
Gradually stir into bouillon.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat. Add yolk to bouillon mixture, stirring constantly.
Pour sauce over meatballs and serve.

title: "apple" crisp
directions: Peel zucchini, cut in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
Cut each piece again in thirds lengthwise.
Slice each of these pieces into 1/4 inch slices which should resemble the shape and size of sliced apples.
Measure 10 cups of zucchini slices and cook, covered in 3/4 cup water, over medium heat until just transparent, 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally and do not overcook.
Drain and cool. Combine cream of tartar, cinnamon, salt, lemon juice and sugar. Add to zucchini and stir.
Place in 7 x 11 pan.

title: nutty buddy pie
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with chocolate graham crackers. Combine milk, peanut butter and cream cheese; mix well.
Add the Cool Whip and blend well.
Spread mixture over the graham crackers.
Pour ice cream syrup on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: party foldovers
directions: Blend flour, margarine and cream cheese.
Chill with a pastry blender.
Place in an airtight container or wrap in plastic wrap and chill overnight.

title: tabouli salad
directions: Saute the wheat in the oil until slightly browned.
Remove from heat; stir in the boiling water.
Cover and let sit for 1 hour, then drain.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese until fluffy. Beat in peanut butter and sugar. Slowly add milk while beating. Add Cool Whip and blend completely. Pour into pie crust and freeze overnight. Thaw in the refrigerator before serving.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Mix together Miracle Whip and sugar.
Set aside.
Layer other ingredients in a large dish in the order listed, using a 9 x 13 glass dish or other size.
(I use a foil pan and layer high.)
Pour Miracle Whip mixture over top.
Do not stir.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: microwave marshmallow creme fudge(makes 72 squares)
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in a buttered large glass mixing bowl; cover.
Microwave on Defrost (Half power) for 15 minutes. Stir and microwave for 8 to 10 minutes or until mixture will form a soft ball in cold water.
Stir in chocolate pieces until chocolate is melted.
Fold in Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: candy bar salad dessert
directions: Beat together all ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Cover and freeze.
