Cut pieces and serve immediately after removing from freezer.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well. Gently fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding and milk; blend in Cool Whip.
Place layer of crackers (whole) on bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Spread half of pudding mixture on top.
Repeat layer of crackers.
Spread the other half of pudding mixture.
Top with crackers and frost. Refrigerate.

title: arkansas enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger in deep pan.
Add 2 cans tomato sauce.
Season with Worcestershire sauce, Louisiana hot sauce, garlic powder, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve over hot water corn bread, sliced in half.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle cheese over top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown beef and onions; add remaining ingredients.
Cook very slow 2 1/2 hours.
Add 6 ounces spaghetti, previously cooked.

title: red velvet cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, butter and vanilla, beating until light.
Gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy.

title: dried beef roll(cheese ball)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread on slices of dried beef.
Roll up and fasten with toothpick.
Chill.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir real good.
Serve over salad.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until well mixed.
Add milk and salt. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: ketchup
directions: Boil juice and onions and paprika down to 3/4 bulk.
Then add all the other ingredients and continue to boil to desired thickness.

title: lima ham dinner
directions: Soak beans overnight in water to cover.
Drain. Combine all ingredients in cooker. Cook on low 8 to 10 hours or
on high 4 to 5 hours.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: garden-style meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Grease two 9 x 5 inch loaf pans. Divide mixture between two loaf pans and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until done and juices run clear. Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: crust for fried pies
directions: Mix together and roll out for fried pies. Canned biscuits may also be use.

title: beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a 9 x 12-inch or 9 x 15-inch pan. Cover with foil.
Bake in oven at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: chicken rice
directions: Put chicken broth, margarine, onion soup and rice in saucepan. Bring to a boil and cook 20 minutes at a simmer until rice is done, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: best breakfast smoothie
directions: Put all ingredients into a Vita Mix machine (or a good blender, but it's not quite the same). Turn on slow, then increase to high speed and blend for 1/2 minute or longer until it's smooth. Serves 2 to 4 people, depending on how much each person wants.

title: island salad
directions: Prepare tossed salad from listed ingredients.
Other salad items can be added based on preference.
Set the salad aside. Saute the picked lobster meat in margarine and Cajun spices. Dress the salad with vinaigrette salad dressing.
Top with the hot lobster meat.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add dill seed and remaining ingredients and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and chill 8 hours.

title: marshmal-o-fudge
directions: Grease 9-inch square pan.
Mix sugar, butter, evaporated milk and Marshmallow Creme in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil quickly, stirring continuously.
Reduce heat and add chips.
Stir until completely melted and blended.
Pour into pan, cool.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix vanilla pudding and pineapple with juice.
Add apples, bananas, oranges and strawberries or grapes.
Mix well.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Stir meal into 2 cups milk.
Let come to a boil, making a mush.
Add remainder of milk, well beaten eggs, salt, baking powder and melted butter.
Bake in a moderate oven for 30 minutes, or until brown.
Serve in dish in which it has been baked.

title: fastest cake in the west
directions: Sift dry ingredients into ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Add pie filling, oil, eggs and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease three 9 x 5-inch loaf pans and divide batter evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (preheated).

title: caramel apple sundae
directions: Divide apple slices equally between two small custard dishes. Place 1/2 tablespoon brown sugar on top of apple slices.
Do not mix.
Microwave both dishes
on High at the same time, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until apple is tender.
Top each dish with a marshmallow.
Microwave on High for 1/4 to 1/2 minute (15 to 30 seconds) or until marshmallow is softened.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze in gallon freezer until firm.

title: grandma mae's coleslaw
directions: Mix cabbage, onion and carrot in a bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; pour over cabbage and mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: bean soup
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage, onion and bell pepper.
Add rest of ingredients and cook slowly for about 1 hour.

title: beverage
directions: Put ice cream in punch bowl and pour 7-Up or Sprite over it. Stir.
Dip and serve.

title: easy spinach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and arrange in flat bowl so you can see all ingredients.
Pour ranch dressing over top of salad in thin lines so dressing does not cover all veggies, then serve. Serves 6 people.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and add cooked shrimp. Marinate in covered container for 6 hours.
Store in refrigerator and serve chilled.

title: japan rice
directions: Friy egg and bacon and cut into pecus.
Make rice and add bacon, egg, unyun and soy sause.
Cuk and eat with chop stiks.

title: chocolate "mini" fudge pies
directions: Mix the ingredients well.
Can pour into 1 pie crust or roll out ready made crust and cut into circles a little larger than bottom of mini muffin pan.
Place circle into each muffin.
Pour filling onto crust and bake at 350° for 25 minutes (will seem wet, but it's not).
Check by inserting toothpick, comes out clean when done.
Makes 24 mini pies or double recipe for 48 pies.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove from bone in small pieces and put in glass dish.
Mix sour cream and soup; spoon over chicken.
Melt margarine and mix with crackers.
Put over chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Add mayonnaise that is desired.

title: dessert made with crackers
directions: Mix together the egg whites, cream of tartar and gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold in the crushed crackers and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool.
Spread with your choice of filling.
Mix 2 packages of Dream Whip.
Spread over top.

title: pickled black-eyed peas
directions: Drain liquid from peas; place peas in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Store in a jar in
the refrigerator for at least 3 days.
Remove garlic after the first day.

title: company potatoes
directions: Saute 1/2 cup onions in butter.
Add soup, potatoes and sour cream.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with 2 cups Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle Durkee onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield: Serves 12 people.

title: rocky road delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine 1/2 cup sugar with the water and cook over medium to medium high heat for 10 minutes. Pour into a 2 quart casserole. Add marshmallow. These will float on top of water. In a mixing bowl, cream together the remaining sugar with the butter. Add vanilla and mix. Combine the flour with the cocoa and add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk. Drop by spoonfuls over marshmallows. Sprinkle with pecans. Bake for 45 minutes. Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip. Also good with ice cream.

title: 24 hour coleslaw
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, oil, salt, celery seed and mustard seed; bring mixture to boil.
Pour over cabbage, onion and green pepper. Cover and refrigerate at once.
Serve the next day.

title: mildred's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 tablespoon sugar in 1/2 cup warm water. Let stand 4 or 5 minutes.
Mix 2 cups warm water, sugar, shortening and salt.
Combine with first mixture and add flour to make a medium dough.
Let stand in warm place until it rises. Then punch down and make into rolls.

title: date balls
directions: Place dates, sugar and margarine in saucepan or large pot. Cook over stove for 5 to 8 minutes.
Take pan off heat and add vanilla.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar or coconut.
This will make about 45 to 50 balls.

title: oyster stew
directions: Cook oysters in their liquid until edges curl, about 5 minutes.
Add milk, margarine or butter, salt, garlic and pepper. Heat, but do not boil.
Serve at once.

title: beef patties with mushroom gravy
directions: Place patties in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chop onion and bell pepper and place on patties.
Pour cold and hot water into pan. Pour gravy mix into water; do not stir.
Cover pan.
Place in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy bake macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions for 5 minutes. Drain well.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until tender; drain and mash.
Add eggs, 3/4 cup sugar, margarine and milk.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Mix the brown sugar, melted margarine and pecan pieces.
Spread on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: green pepper steak
directions: With a very sharp knife cut beef across grain into thin stips 1/8 in. thick.
Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger.
Add to beef, toss and set aside while preparing vegetables.

Heat oil in large frying pan or wok, add beef and toss over high heat until browned. Taste meat, if not tender cover and simmer for 30-40 min. over low heat. Turn heat up and add vegetables are tender crisp about 10 min.
Mix cornstarch with water. Add to pan; stir and cook until thickened. Add tomatoes and heat through.
Good served over rice.

title: bill's holiday cheese ball
directions: Mash cheese with a fork.
Stir in pineapple that is completely drained.
Add remaining ingredients except nuts.
Shape into ball. Roll in chopped nuts.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: fiesta zucchini
directions: Heat olive oil in heavy skillet over medium-low heat.
Add zucchini, garlic and oregano and saute until garlic is just golden (about 2 minutes).
Add salsa and simmer until zucchini is just tender (about 6 minutes).
Reduce heat to low; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and cook until cheese melts.

title: strawberry jelly
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving syrup.
Measure 3/4 cup syrup, adding water if necessary.
Mix pectin and water in large saucepan.
Bring to a full, rolling boil and boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low; stir in syrup and sugar.
Heat, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Do not boil.
Add a few drops of coloring.
Remove from heat and skim off foam with metal spoon.

title: barbecued turkey legs
directions: Sprinkle
turkey with salt and pepper.	Place in crock-pot. Combine remaining ingredients;
pour over turkey.
Cover and cook on	low
for 5 to 7 hours.	If turkey legs are small, serve one thigh
or
one
drumstick per person.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: desperation meal
directions: Brown chops and onion in large skillet.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Cook for 20 minutes over low heat.
Add wild rice to chops using 1/2 amount of the water called for on package.
Stir well.
Cook covered for 30 minutes until liquid is gone.
Serves 4 to 6. You may substitute chicken for the pork chops, but the skin should be removed.

title: raspberry wings
directions: At least 3 hours before serving, marinate wings in mixture of all other ingredients.
Turn to coat all wings.
Use Pam to spray rack over cookie sheet.
Add wings.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: crab noodle salad
directions: Mix all ingredients listed in a medium-large bowl.
Let set until chilled in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 6 to 8 persons.

title: chili dip
directions: Combine chili and cream cheese in pan.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sauce and olives.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and thinly slice.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add flour, salt & pepper.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 more minutes.
Stir in cheese and remove from heat.
In greased casserole, layer half the potatoes and cover with half the sauce.
Repeat.
Bake, covered, at 350 degrees for 45 minutes, stirring once.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes.

title: ham ball
directions: Let cheese soften
to
room
temperature.
Chop ham and onions. Combine first
ingredients together. Roll in ground pecans. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar; sprinkle over pudding.
Place in oven (400°) or broiler long enough to just slightly brown the top. Sprinkle pudding with crushed almonds.
Serve chilled.
It's good!

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Combine broth, soy sauce and cornstarch and set aside.
Heat oil in skillet; add garlic and ginger; cook 1/2 minute, then add slowest cooking vegies first.
Add rest of vegies.
When vegies are crisp, but tender, add meat (skinless) and broth mixture. Cook until bubbly and serve immediately over rice or cooked noodles.
Serves 2.

title: holiday pie
directions: Cream cheese; add milk.
Blend.
Add sour cream and mix.
Add other ingredients and blend until smooth.
Spoon into an 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with Triscuits, saltines or Fritos.

title: angel cake - chocolate
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler; cool.
Add egg yolks only. Beat egg whites until stiff and add to chocolate mixture.
Add whipped cream, sugar, salt, nuts and vanilla.
Tear or cut cake into small pieces.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish with cake.
Add a layer of chocolate, then cake, then chocolate, ending with chocolate.
Refrigerate until very cold.
If keeping overnight, cover with foil.
May top with whipped cream, nuts and cherries, if desired.

title: creole chicken with garlic
directions: Heat oil over medium-high heat in Dutch oven.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Cook in batches in hot oil until brown.
Set aside.
Reduce heat to medium and add garlic, onions, peppers and 1 teaspoon salt and cook until soft, about 10 minutes. Increase heat to high; add wine and cook until all liquid evaporates.
Add tomatoes, oregano, cayenne and chicken.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until chicken is tender, 45 to 60 minutes. Taste and adjust seasoning.
If sauce is too thin, remove chicken and cook sauce over high heat until thickened.

title: pecan surprises
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bake at 350° until very lightly browned.

title: easy french onion soup
directions: Melt the butter or margarine in a large saucepan.
Add onions; saute for 3 to 4 minutes, until light brown.
Add the consomme, water and Worcestershire sauce; bring to a boil.
Turn the heat down slightly; simmer for 45 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and a pinch of sugar to taste.
Pour into 4 individual ovenproof bowls with a soup ladle until the bowls are 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Place bread on top of the soup bowl; sprinkle with cheese.
Put the bowls on a strong baking sheet; broil until the cheese begins to bubble.

title: green punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl and chill.

title: peanut butter cup bars
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs with melted butter.
Mix in peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Mix thoroughly and pat evenly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate over warm, not hot, water and spread over the cracker mixture.
Cool in refrigerator.
Cool until chocolate is firm.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together and freeze in individual molds until firm.
Take out of freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: party punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in kettle. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill. Serve over ice.
Makes about 40 servings.

title: shrimp dip(for vegies or crackers)
directions: Mix well with electric beater.
Chill. Serve as spread or dip for raw vegetables or crackers.

title: white cookies
directions: Mix all together. Sprinkle dough with sugar and refrigerate overnight. Roll out about 1/4 inch thick and cut with cookie cutter. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin dream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add combined oats and flour, mix well.
Spread evenly onto bottom of pan.
Bake 18-20 minutes or till light brown.
Cool slightly.
Beat cream cheese and sugar at medium speed till fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add remaining ingredients, mix till smooth.
Pour over partially cooled crust.
Bake an additional 45-50 minutes or till center appears set.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream if desired.
Makes 20 bars.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Combine ingredients in a large glass or stainless steel bowl. Put in refrigerator for 3 days; stir once a day.
Then put in freezer boxes and freeze.
Allow to thaw, then serve.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Trim off chops and brown on both sides.
In shallow baking dish, mix rice, water, salt and pepper, onion and undiluted soup. Add green pepper.
Arrange chops in dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hawaiian vegetables
directions: Combine carrots, onions, green pepper and celery.
Cook until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain well.
In a saucepan, combine salt, water, sugar, brown sugar, cornstarch, vinegar, cinnamon and cloves with pineapple juice, drained from can of pineapple.
Cook until thick.
Add water chestnuts, drained and sliced, and pineapple chunks.
Add to sauce; then add to vegetables and heat.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix in the same order as listed.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine everything except spinach, eggs and bacon in a container with a tight fitting lid and shake well.
Place spinach, bacon and chopped eggs in bowl and pour in enough dressing to moisten.

title: microwave ravioli casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole, stir water into flour; stir in broth. Micro-cook uncovered until thickened and bubbly, about 5 minutes, stirring after each minute.
Stir in the ravioli in sauce, beef, beans and mushrooms.
Micro-cook covered until hot, 7 to 8 minutes, stirring four times.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; set aside.
Cut cheese into squares. Melt margarine and pour over cheese.
Pour over crushed crackers. Place broccoli in 9 x 13-inch pan and top with cheese mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Bring the milk to a boil and slowly stir in the cornmeal.
Add the ginger and salt and continue to heat for about 15 minutes, until cornmeal has thickened.
Add the molasses, butter and egg. Mix well and pour into a buttered baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for about 40 minutes.
Serve warm; top with whip cream, if desired.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs, butter and water.
Cook until thick. Add vinegar and lemon extract.
Pour in cooked pie shell.
Add meringue.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes, green peppers, hot peppers, onions, garlic powder and oregano until tender.
Blend in blender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until it begins to thicken.
Put in jars. Process 15 minutes in boiling water bath (start timing after it comes to a full boil).

title: greek rice pudding
directions: In saucepan, add milk, water and salt.
At boiling point, add rice and put on low heat.
Boil rice for 45 minutes, stirring often.
Let rice cool 15 minutes.
In a bowl, add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat real well and add to the rice mixture and mix well. Put in serving cups, sprinkle top with cinnamon and refrigerate.

title: chicken 'n beef
directions: Spray light coat of Pam on bottom of roasting pan or Pyrex dish.
Line bottom of pan with dried beef.
Wrap each chicken breast with 1 uncooked bacon strip.
Place breasts in pan over dried beef.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup together and spread over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour (or until done).
Serve with green vegetables, wild rice and dinner rolls.

title: peach-glazed chicken with stuffing
directions: Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Add enough water to make 1 cup; set aside.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add chicken and brown.
Add water-syrup mixture, sugar, vinegar and spices.
Bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in stuffing mix and peaches; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce; simmer 15 minutes.
Put biscuits in muffin pan, pressing bottom and sides. Add sauce; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: peaches and cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatins in boiling water in bowl.
Spoon in ice cream, stirring until melted.
Chill in refrigerator until partially set.
Add peaches; mix well.
Pour into serving dish; chill until set.
Yields 12 servings.

title: avocado pie
directions: Mix well avocado, milk and lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell. Refrigerate for 4 hours before serving.
Can be topped with whipped cream.

title: jefferson davis raisin pie
directions: Mix in mixer and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: captain's delight
directions: Melt butterscotch bits in double boiler.
Combine rest in melted bits.
Cool 30 minutes.
Store in tight container.

title: bread pudding
directions: Toast firm white bread in cubes on baking sheet until golden brown; cool.
Soak 1/2 cup raisins in hot water.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Whisk together eggs in large mixing bowl, then gradually whisk in sugar mixture.
Whisk in 6 cups milk and vanilla extract.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt butter, add drained oysters and cook 3 minutes or until the edges curl.
Add milk, salt, pepper and liquid oysters and bring almost, but not quite, to a boil.
Serve.
Dust with paprika.

title: savory baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in large casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Uncover casserole the last 30 minutes.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain all fruit very well (approximately 1 to 2 hours).
Mix all fruit, except applesauce.
Put fruit into a 2-quart casserole and top with applesauce.
Sprinkle with spices and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until well heated.
Serves 8.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix dry gelatin and cottage cheese. Add pineapple and oranges. Fold in whipped topping.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: delores' peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut peaches into bite-size chunks and pour peaches and liquid into pan.
Mix Bisquick, sugar and milk.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Slice tomatoes last and mix well.
Refrigerate to chill.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix Wesson oil, sugar and eggs. Cream. Mix dry ingredients and add to other mixture.
Chop apples and nuts.
Add to mixture. Line loaf pan with wax paper.
Cook 60 minutes at 350°.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread graham crackers evenly on top.

Spread in layers coconut, chocolate chips and chopped nuts. Drizzle Eagle Brand milk evenly on top (or other sweetened condensed milk).	Let stand for 1/4 to 1/2 hour.	Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: scalded lettuce
directions: In bowl, dice onions in center on top of lettuce.
Set aside. Mix vinegar ingredients in
saucepan.
Bring to a rapid boil. Boil 1 minute and immediately pour directly on the onions.
Then lift and toss lettuce well.

title: miracle peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 11-inch pan in a 350° oven.
Combine next four ingredients in a medium-sized mixing bowl.
Add milk and blend well.
Pour mixture into pan.
Spoon peaches and juice over batter; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: rotel tomatoes and rice
directions: Pour ingredients in dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes.

title: kookie brittle
directions: Mix together ingredients and spread on a heavy cookie sheet. Bake for about 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.
Watch very closely as it burns easily.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add all others.
Heat iron skillet until hot, then pour batter into it and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hot cranberry crunch
directions: Mix cranberries, apples and sugar together and put into greased casserole.
Put the following ingredients on top (in order): oatmeal, brown sugar, pecans and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add remaining dry ingredients and stir.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: hillbilly cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Combine raisins, sugar, butter, water, cinnamon and allspice in a saucepan.
Boil for two minutes. Add 2 c. flour, baking soda, and pecans.
Mix thoroughly; pour into a 9 inch x 13 inch greased pan.
Spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325 degrees.
Meanwhile, combine melted butter, brown sugar, coconut, 1 tbsp. flour, 1 cup pecans and cream.
Mix well.
Remove cake from oven; spread with frosting.
Return to oven and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry pudding mix. Stir gently, but mix well. Add
marshmallows
and
undrained pineapple;
mix well. Spread in Pyrex
dish
and chill several hours before serving. Cut into squares to serve.
Top each square with a cherry.
If desired, peaches and bananas can be added.

title: dutch pea soup (erwten soep) with beef
directions: A great meal when the Tule Fog rolls in!
Wash and clean peas. Soak overnight.
In morning, bring to a boil, turn on low and add all ingredients.
Simmer for about 6 hours.
Remove from stove, cool and remove meat and bones.
Take all soup, small amount at a time and put it through food processor.
Return to pan.
Add meat that has been cut into small pieces and a large round beef sausage and salt and pepper.
Heat soup on warm to medium (not high, it will burn) until sausage is done.
Ready to eat or ready to freeze (after cooling).
Before eating or freezing, cut up sausage.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix above ingredients except cornflakes and put in 9x9 pan. Sprinkle corn flakes over the top of potato mixture and drizzle with melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: stack cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients except sugar and spices.
Cream together sugar, eggs, buttermilk, shortening, vanilla and spices. Gently combine creamed and dry ingredients using a fork.
Batter will resemble biscuit dough.
Set aside 1/2.
Grease and flour 4 (9-inch) cake pans.
Divide each half a second time.
Put each quarter of dough into cake pan and bake in oven preheated to 350° until golden brown, if made with molasses, or light brown if not, about 20 minutes.
Layers will be thin.
Remove cake layers from pans.
Put cooked apples between each layer.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Combine butter and cheese in saucepan and melt over low heat. Remove
from
heat;
add
chips
and heat until melted. Remove from
heat	and
beat
in
sugar gradually.
Add salt, vanilla and
nuts.	Put
into
an
8-inch square greased pan. Store in refrigerator about 2 hours and then cut into squares.

title: maple peanut yummies
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend with a mixer.
Shape into balls, using a rounded teaspoonful.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets after they have been flattened with a fork, crisscross fashion.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Makes 48 to 54 cookies.

title: jalapeno white sauce
directions: Heat whipping cream in a heavy saucepan over heat.
When the cream in ready to boil, stir in sour cream. After sour cream dissolves, reduce heat to medium. Stir in chicken base and Jalapeo juice and simmer.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, cocoa and water in 2 cup glass bowl or measuring cup.
Cook on High for 2 minutes*; stir every 30 seconds.
Add butter and cook additional 30 seconds.
Stir; add vanilla and salt.

title: chocolate-caramel brownies
directions: Heat caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Combine cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Press half of mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake 6 minutes. Remove from oven. Sprinkle with chocolate chips. Drizzle with melted caramels. Crumble remaining 1/2 of cake mixture over the top. Bake 15 to 18 minutes. Do not overbake. Cool 30 minutes in fridge before cutting.

title: chili soup
directions: Render suet. Fry ground beef and onions until brown. Boil together with tomatoes, beans and needed water.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut
biscuits into fourths, using scissors.
Mix cinnamon and sugar in plastic bag; toss biscuit pieces in bag until well coated.
Layer
biscuit
pieces
in
a well-greased Bundt pan, sprinkling
pecans
between layers.
Melt brown sugar and margarine together; pour over contents of pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cindy's gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; mix flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to shortening mixture; add well beaten eggs.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll into balls and flatten with fingers into about 1 1/2-inches in diameter and pretty thick. Bake until done at 400° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine the oil, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Sift together 2 cups flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, allspice and cloves. Add to oil mixture alternately with apple juice.
Mix the other cup of flour with the fruits and nuts.
Add fruits to batter and mix well.
Pour in two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans, greased and lined with brown paper.
Place pan of water on lower rack of oven.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Cool before removing paper. Glaze.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Make jello using half the water required, let jello set. Mix dream whip according to package directions, whip cream cheese into dream whip, beat dream whip mixture into jello. Fold pineapple and nuts into mixture. Pour into mold
and let set.

title: cheesy rice and broccoli
directions: Bring broccoli and water to boil in medium saucepan, separating broccoli with fork.
Stir in Velveeta cheese spread. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes.

title: fool's toffee
directions: In small saucepan over medium heat, blend butter and brown sugar.
Heat to boiling and boil for 4 minutes.
Cover 10 x 15-inch jelly pan with foil and butter lightly.
Place single layer of crackers on foil close together.
Pour butter mixture over crackers, spreading evenly.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Microwave chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter in 1-quart microwavable bowl uncovered on High for 1 minute; stir. Microwave 30 seconds longer or until mixture can be stirred smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal in bowl, stirring until evenly coated.
Pour half of mixture into a gallon size storage bag; add 1/2 of the powdered sugar.
Seal bag and shake until cereal is well coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool; store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Repeat steps with other half of mixture.

title: bean soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook over medium heat for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, until beans are soft.
Add water as needed to maintain quantity.
Soup is thick and rich; good for cold winter day, served with fresh, hot rolls.

title: banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press into bottom of pan.
Arrange banana slices on crust.
Beat cream cheese in a large bowl with a wire whisk until smooth.
Beat in milk.
Add pudding mixes.
Mix well.
Spread evenly over banana slices.
Spoon pineapple evenly over pudding mixture.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Chill 3 hours until ready to serve.
Makes 15 servings.

title: brewed iced tea
directions: In a large saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Pour into heat-proof pitcher or bowl.
Add tea bags, cover and steep for 4 minutes; remove tea bags.
Add sugar as desired to taste.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and 1/2
cup
powdered sugar.
Cut butter into flour mixture with a pastry blender or fork, until resembles coarse meal.
Spoon flour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press firmly with fingertips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until crust is slightly browned.
Cool.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into graham cracker crusts. Refrigerate at least 30 minutes before serving.
Can also freeze. Makes 2 pies.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all of the above and bake at 375 degrees.

title: yummy balls
directions: Mix all and form into balls.
Chill.
Melt one large and one small bag of chocolate chips and 1/2 cake of paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls and chill.

title: marinated potato and mushroom salad
directions: In a large shallow dish or plastic bay, combine oil, juice, mustard, sugar and bouillon.
Mix well.
Add potatoes, mushrooms, celery and green onions.
Cover.
Marinate in refrigerator 3 hours or overnight, stirring occasionally. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: vegetable gumbo
directions: Mix all together and boil until tender.
Season with garlic powder and salt and pepper.
